687	process for transferees?	Absolutely! We welcome transfer students! Here's everything you need to know about transferring to LCC!\n\n<strong>TRANSFEREE REQUIREMENTS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> <strong>Transcript of Records (TOR)</strong> from your previous college  \n<strong>2.</strong> <strong>Certificate of Eligibility to Transfer</strong> (if still enrolled)  \n<strong>3.</strong> <strong>Certificate of Good Moral Character</strong> from previous school  \n<strong>4.</strong> <strong>PSA Birth Certificate</strong> (original)  \n<strong>5.</strong> <strong>2-3 pieces of 2x2 ID photos</strong>  \n\n<strong>THE PROCESS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> <strong>Submit your TOR to the Registrar</strong>  \nThey will evaluate which subjects are creditable  \n\n<strong>2.</strong> <strong>Meet with your program's Dean</strong>  \nDiscuss your curriculum and required subjects  \n\n<strong>3.</strong> <strong>Submit admission requirements</strong>  \nFollow the same process as new students  \n\n<strong>4.</strong> <strong>Complete enrollment</strong>  \nPay fees and finalize your schedule  \n\n<strong>IMPORTANT THINGS TO KNOW:</strong>  \n\n<strong>SUBJECT CREDITING:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Not all subjects automatically transfer  \n<strong>2.</strong> The Registrar evaluates based on course content  \n<strong>3.</strong> Similar subjects may be credited  \n<strong>4.</strong> Some subjects may need to be retaken  \n\n<strong>PROCESSING TIME:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Getting TOR from previous school: 1 to 2 weeks  \n<strong>2.</strong> LCC evaluation: A few days to 1 week  \n\n<strong>BEST TIME TO TRANSFER:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Start of the semester (1st or 2nd semester)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Allows smoother transition  \n\n<strong>NEED MORE INFORMATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Contact the <strong>Registrar's Office</strong>  \n<strong>2.</strong> Contact the <strong>Dean</strong> of your chosen program  \n<strong>3.</strong> Visit: https://www.lipacitycolleges.edu.ph/  \n\nWhich program are you planning to transfer into? I can guide you to the right office!	transfer_student_process	67.65681084589575	2026-03-29 12:48:04.561007+08	\N
688	[Clicked: Tuition payment options and terms]	Great question! I understand that managing tuition payments is important for families.\n\nYes! Lipa City Colleges offers <strong>flexible payment options</strong> to help students.\n\n<strong>TYPICAL PAYMENT SCHEMES:</strong>  \n<strong>FULL PAYMENT:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Pay everything at the start of the semester  \n<strong>2.</strong> May include early payment discounts  \n\n<strong>INSTALLMENT PLANS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Usually 2 to 3 installments per semester  \n<strong>2.</strong> Pay at scheduled intervals throughout the term  \n<strong>3.</strong> Most common option for families  \n\n<strong>TERM PAYMENT:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Pay before midterms, finals, or other scheduled periods  \n<strong>2.</strong> Spread payments across the semester  \n\n<strong>IMPORTANT NOTES:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Payment terms may vary depending on:  \n   • Year level  \n   • Program enrolled in  \n   • Current semester policies  \n\n<strong>2.</strong> Payment deadlines must be followed to avoid penalties  \n\n<strong>TO GET EXACT PAYMENT TERMS:</strong>  \n\n<strong>1.</strong> Visit or contact the <strong>Cashier's Office</strong>  \n   • They will explain current payment options  \n   • Provide the payment schedule  \n   • Calculate your total fees  \n\n<strong>PRO TIP:</strong> Talk to the Cashier during enrollment. They can help you find a payment plan that works best for your family.\n\n<strong>GOOD NEWS:</strong> We also offer <strong>scholarship programs</strong> that can reduce your tuition by 25% to 100%.\n\nWould you like to know more about these scholarship options? They can make payments even easier!	payment_terms	67.98531070706778	2026-03-29 12:49:30.689033+08	\N
689	how to apply for scholarship	I'm glad you're interested in our scholarships! Let me guide you through the application process!\n\n<strong>STEP-BY-STEP APPLICATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> <strong>Visit the Marketing Office</strong>  \nLocated on campus  \nOffice hours: Monday to Saturday, 8:00 AM to 5:00 PM  \n\n<strong>2.</strong> <strong>Submit requirements</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Scholarship application form (available at the Marketing Office)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Form 138 (for academic scholarships)  \n<strong>3.</strong> Supporting documents depending on scholarship type:  \n   • Solo Parent ID (for Solo Parent Discount)  \n   • Parent's Alumni Certificate (for Alumni Discount)  \n   • Barangay Certificate (for some programs)  \n   • etc.  \n\n<strong>3.</strong> <strong>Wait for evaluation</strong>  \nThe office reviews your application  \nProcessing time usually takes a few days to one week  \n\n<strong>4.</strong> <strong>Receive approval</strong>  \nIf approved, you will be notified  \nYou will receive a scholarship grant letter  \n\n<strong>5.</strong> <strong>Proceed with enrollment</strong>  \nThe scholarship discount will be applied during enrollment  \nIt will appear on your assessment form  \n\n<strong>DIFFERENT SCHOLARSHIPS, DIFFERENT PROCESSES:</strong>  \n\n<strong>ACADEMIC SCHOLARSHIP:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Automatic for qualifying GPA  \n<strong>2.</strong> Submit Form 138 showing grades  \n\n<strong>GOVERNMENT SCHOLARSHIPS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Apply directly to the government office (CHED, Mayor's Office, etc.)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Submit requirements to them first, then inform LCC  \n\n<strong>SPECIAL SCHOLARSHIPS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Submit proof of eligibility  \n<strong>2.</strong> May require an interview  \n\n<strong>IMPORTANT TIPS:</strong>  \n\n<strong>1.</strong> Apply early as some scholarships have limited slots  \n<strong>2.</strong> Apply before enrollment for better chances 