708	what is eba scholarship	Excellent! Let me tell you about government scholarships available to LCC students!\n\n<strong>AVAILABLE GOVERNMENT SCHOLARSHIPS:</strong>  \n\n<strong>1. MAYOR ERIC B. AFRICA (EBA) SCHOLARSHIP:</strong>  \n\n<strong>WHO CAN QUALIFY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Student residents of Lipa City  \n<strong>2.</strong> Must be a registered resident  \n\n<strong>BENEFITS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> 100% tuition fee discount for one semester  \n\n<strong>HOW TO MAINTAIN:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Maintain a GPA of 2.0 or better  \n<strong>2.</strong> No individual grade lower than 3.00 (except PE and NSTP)  \n<strong>3.</strong> Maintain good academic standing  \n\n<strong>WHERE TO APPLY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Lipa City Mayor's Office  \n<strong>2.</strong> Submit approved documents to LCC Scholarships Office  \n\n<strong>REQUIREMENTS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Barangay Certificate (proof of residency)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Latest grades  \n<strong>3.</strong> Application form from the Mayor's Office  \n\n<strong>2. PROVINCIAL CAPITOL SCHOLARSHIP AND FINANCIAL ASSISTANCE:</strong>  \n\n<strong>WHO CAN QUALIFY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Students residing in Batangas Province  \n<strong>2.</strong> Applicants from any municipality in Batangas  \n\n<strong>BENEFITS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Scholarship grants  \n<strong>2.</strong> Financial assistance  \n<strong>3.</strong> Amount varies depending on the program  \n\n<strong>PROVIDED BY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Office of the Governor  \n<strong>2.</strong> Board Members of the 6th District of Batangas  \n\n<strong>WHERE TO APPLY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Provincial Capitol of Batangas  \n<strong>2.</strong> Submit approved documents to LCC  \n\n<strong>REQUIREMENTS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Requirements set by the Provincial Capitol  \n<strong>2.</strong> Proof of Batangas residency  \n<strong>3.</strong> Academic records  \n\n<strong>3. CHED SCHOLARSHIPS:</strong>  \n\n<strong>WHAT THESE INCLUDE:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> CHED-TDP or Tertiary Education Subsidy  \n<strong>2.</strong> CHED-TES or Tertiary Education Subsidy  \n<strong>3.</strong> Other CHED scholarship programs  \n\n<strong>WHO CAN QUALIFY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Depends on the specific program  \n<strong>2.</strong> Usually based on income, academic performance, and financial need  \n\n<strong>BENEFITS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Full or partial tuition coverage  \n<strong>2.</strong> Financial assistance  \n<strong>3.</strong> Possible allowances depending on the program  \n\n<strong>WHERE TO APPLY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> CHED Office  \n<strong>2.</strong> UNIFAST Portal  \n<strong>3.</strong> LCC Linkages Office for guidance  \n\n<strong>WHEN TO APPLY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Usually at the start of the school year  \n<strong>2.</strong> Follow official CHED announcements  \n\n<strong>ADVANTAGES OF GOVERNMENT SCHOLARSHIPS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Can be combined with LCC institutional scholarships  \n<strong>2.</strong> May cover more than tuition, including allowances  \n<strong>3.</strong> No repayment required  \n\n<strong>HOW TO APPLY:</strong>  \n\n<strong>1.</strong> Check eligibility requirements  \n<strong>2.</strong> Apply directly to the government office  \n<strong>3.</strong> Submit approval documents to LCC Scholarships Office  \n\n<strong>WHERE TO GET ASSISTANCE:</strong>  \n\n<strong>1.</strong> LCC Linkages Office  \n<strong>2.</strong> LCC Scholarships Office  \n\n<strong>PRO TIPS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Apply early due to limited slots  \n<strong>2.</strong> Maintain good academic performance  \n<strong>3.</strong> Explore multiple scholarship options  \n<strong>4.</strong> Renew on time to avoid losing benefits  	about_government_scholarships	69.37478361454846	2026-03-29 20:46:18.200205+08	\N
709	do you have carlos mojares scholarship?	Let me tell you about the Carlos R. Mojares Scholarship Program!\n\n<strong>WHAT IS IT:</strong>  \nThe Carlos R. Mojares Scholarship is named after a former LCC President known for his approachable leadership and dedication to helping others. This scholarship is awarded to outstanding student leaders who demonstrate strong character in school and in the community.\n\n<strong>WHO CAN QUALIFY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Outstanding student leaders  \n<strong>2.</strong> Must be in good standing in school and community  \n<strong>3.</strong> Must maintain required academic performance  \n\n<strong>SCHOLARSHIP BENEFITS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> 100% discount on tuition fee  \n<strong>2.</strong> Covers tuition fee only (does not include miscellaneous fees)  \n\n<strong>DURATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Renewable until program completion, provided requirements are maintained  \n\n<strong>HOW TO MAINTAIN THE SCHOLARSHIP:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> No grades lower than 2.50 in any subject  \n<strong>2.</strong> Maintain a GPA of 2.25 or higher  \n<strong>3.</strong> Remain in good standing with no disciplinary actions  \n<strong>4.</strong> Submit a certified true copy of your latest grades  \n\n<strong>RENEWAL BENEFITS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> 100% discount on tuition fee as long as qualifications are met  \n\n<strong>REQUIREMENTS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Certified true copy of latest grades  \n<strong>2.</strong> Proof of student leadership involvement  \n<strong>3.</strong> Scholarship application or renewal form  \n\n<strong>WHERE TO APPLY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Scholarships Office  \n<strong>2.</strong> Marketing Office  \n\n<strong>PRO TIP:</strong>  \nThis scholarship is ideal for students who are active in student organizations, student councils, or community service activities.\n\nWould you like to know about other scholarships available at LCC? Just ask!	about_carlos_mojares_scholarship	71.23742470353096	2026-03-29 20:50:02.1294+08	\N
710	what scholarship do you offer?	<strong>Institutional Scholarships (From the School)</strong>\r\n• Academic Scholarship - Get 25% to 100% discount based on your grades! The better your GPA, the bigger the discount.\r\n• Gawad Karunungan - Full scholarship for our most outstanding students\r\n• Carlos R. Mojares Leadership Scholarship - Full tuition discount if you're a student leader\r\n• Family Privilege - Discounts when multiple family members enroll together\r\n• Solo Parent Discount - 20% off for students with solo parents\r\n• Alumni Discount - 20% off if your parent graduated from LCC\r\n• AYOUDA Program - 50% discount for students from distant areas\r\n• BEAP - 50% discount for students affected by the Taal eruption\r\n\r\n<strong>Government Scholarships</strong>\r\n• Mayor Eric B. Africa (EBA) Scholarship - For qualified Lipa City residents\r\n• Provincial Capitol Scholarship - Provincial government assistance\r\n• CHED Scholarships - National-level grants\r\n\r\n<strong>How to Apply</strong>\r\nJust visit our Marketing Office and submit your application! They'll guide you through the process.\r\n\r\nFor specific requirements, deadlines, or to know which scholarship fits you best, you can also check with the Student Affairs Office or the Guidance & Admission Office. They're super helpful!\r\n\r\nWould you like to know more about the admission requirements or enrollment process? I'm here to help! 😊	scholarship_programs	70.42118348729792	2026-03-29 22:23:40.83085+08	\N
711	scholarship program?	That's our most prestigious scholarship! Let me tell you about Gawad Karunungan!\n\n<strong>WHAT IS GAWAD KARUNUNGAN:</strong>  \nThis is LCC's <strong>full scholarship program</strong> and the highest honor offered by the institution. It covers 100% of both tuition and miscellaneous fees.\n\n<strong>WHAT MAKES IT SPECIAL:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Known as "Gawad Karunungan," meaning Award of Knowledge or Wisdom  \n<strong>2.</strong> Considered the most prestigious scholarship of LCC  \n<strong>3.</strong> Provides 100% full scholarship coverage  \n<strong>4.</strong> Offered only during milestone years  \n\n<strong>WHO CAN QUALIFY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Students with outstanding academic performance  \n<strong>2.</strong> Active participation in socio-civic and community activities  \n<strong>3.</strong> Demonstrates upright character and good conduct  \n<strong>4.</strong> Comes from a financially deserving or indigent background  \n\n<strong>WHAT IT COVERS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> 100% tuition fee  \n<strong>2.</strong> 100% miscellaneous fees  \n<strong>3.</strong> No out-of-pocket expenses for tuition  \n\n<strong>WHEN IT IS OFFERED:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> During milestone years, typically every 5 years  \n<strong>2.</strong> Usually aligned with major anniversaries of LCC  \n\n<strong>IMPORTANT NOTES:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Not a regular yearly scholarship  \n<strong>2.</strong> Offered only on special occasions  \n<strong>3.</strong> Limited slots and highly competitive  \n<strong>4.</strong> Intended for exceptional and deserving students  \n\n<strong>HOW TO APPLY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Watch for official announcements during milestone years  \n<strong>2.</strong> Contact the Scholarships Office to check availability  \n<strong>3.</strong> Inquire if it is currently a milestone year for this scholarship  \n\n<strong>IF NOT AVAILABLE THIS YEAR:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Academic Scholarship for top 1 to 5 students  \n<strong>2.</strong> Dr. Ricardo Bonilla Scholarship (up to 100%)  \n<strong>3.</strong> AYOUDA or BEAP programs (up to 50% for qualified students)  \n<strong>4.</strong> Other available scholarship programs  \n\nWould you like to explore other scholarship options? I can help you find one that fits your situation.	about_gawad_karunungan	73.86542753517662	2026-03-29 22:26:30.666446+08	\N
712	what scholarship program do you offeR?	<strong>INSTITUTIONAL SCHOLARSHIPS (FROM THE SCHOOL):</strong>  \n\n<strong>1.</strong> <strong>Academic Scholarship</strong> - Get 25% to 100% discount based on your grades. Higher GPA means higher discount  \n<strong>2.</strong> <strong>Gawad Karunungan</strong> - Full scholarship for outstanding students  \n<strong>3.</strong> <strong>Carlos R. Mojares Leadership Scholarship</strong> - Full tuition discount for student leaders  \n<strong>4.</strong> <strong>Family Privilege</strong> - Discounts for families with multiple enrolled members  \n<strong>5.</strong> <strong>Solo Parent Discount</strong> - 20% tuition discount for students with solo parents  \n<strong>6.</strong> <strong>Alumni Discount</strong> - 20% tuition discount if a parent graduated from LCC  \n<strong>7.</strong> <strong>AYOUDA Program</strong> - 50% tuition discount for students from distant areas  \n<strong>8.</strong> <strong>BEAP</strong> - 50% tuition discount for students affected by the Taal eruption  \n\n<strong>GOVERNMENT SCHOLARSHIPS:</strong>  \n\n<strong>1.</strong> <strong>Mayor Eric B. Africa (EBA) Scholarship</strong> - For qualified Lipa City residents  \n<strong>2.</strong> <strong>Provincial Capitol Scholarship</strong> - Assistance from the provincial government  \n<strong>3.</strong> <strong>CHED Scholarships</strong> - National-level scholarship programs  \n\n<strong>HOW TO APPLY:</strong>  \n\n<strong>1.</strong> Visit the Marketing Office and submit your application  \n<strong>2.</strong> Follow the guidance provided by the staff  \n\nFor specific requirements, deadlines, or to find the best scholarship for you, you may also visit the Student Affairs Office or the Guidance and Admission Office.\n\nWould you like to know more about admission requirements or the enrollment process? I'm here to help!	scholarship_programs	70.70552874771666	2026-03-29 22:26:51.378931+08	\N
713	what is computer science	Awesome! Let me tell you about our Computer and Technology programs!\n\n<strong>YES, WE OFFER TWO TECH PROGRAMS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> <strong>Bachelor of Science in Computer Science (BSCS)</strong>  \n<strong>2.</strong> <strong>Bachelor of Science in Computer Engineering (BSCPE)</strong>  \n\n<strong>WHAT IS THE DIFFERENCE:</strong>  \n\n<strong>BSCS (Computer Science) - SOFTWARE FOCUS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Programming and coding  \n<strong>2.</strong> Software development  \n<strong>3.</strong> Application development  \n<strong>4.</strong> Web development  \n<strong>5.</strong> Database management  \n<strong>6.</strong> Artificial Intelligence and machine learning  \n\n<strong>BSCPE (Computer Engineering) - HARDWARE AND SOFTWARE:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Computer systems  \n<strong>2.</strong> Electronics and circuits  \n<strong>3.</strong> Embedded systems  \n<strong>4.</strong> Networking and hardware  \n<strong>5.</strong> Robotics  \n<strong>6.</strong> System design  \n\n<strong>PROGRAM DETAILS:</strong>  \n\n<strong>DURATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Both programs take 4 years (8 semesters)  \n\n<strong>WHAT YOU WILL STUDY (BSCS):</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Programming (Java, Python, C++, and others)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Data Structures and Algorithms  \n<strong>3.</strong> Database Management  \n<strong>4.</strong> Web Development  \n<strong>5.</strong> Mobile Application Development  \n<strong>6.</strong> Software Engineering  \n<strong>7.</strong> Cybersecurity  \n<strong>8.</strong> Artificial Intelligence fundamentals  \n\n<strong>WHAT YOU WILL STUDY (BSCPE):</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Digital Logic Design  \n<strong>2.</strong> Computer Architecture  \n<strong>3.</strong> Microprocessors  \n<strong>4.</strong> Electronics and Circuits  \n<strong>5.</strong> Network Engineering  \n<strong>6.</strong> Embedded Systems  \n<strong>7.</strong> Programming  \n\n<strong>FACILITIES:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Modern computer laboratories  \n<strong>2.</strong> High-speed internet  \n<strong>3.</strong> Updated software and tools  \n<strong>4.</strong> Air-conditioned computer rooms  \n\n<strong>AFTER GRADUATION:</strong>  \n\n<strong>CAREER OPPORTUNITIES (BSCS):</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Software Developer or Programmer  \n<strong>2.</strong> Web Developer  \n<strong>3.</strong> Mobile Application Developer  \n<strong>4.</strong> Database Administrator  \n<strong>5.</strong> Cybersecurity Specialist  \n<strong>6.</strong> AI or Machine Learning Engineer  \n<strong>7.</strong> Game Developer  \n<strong>8.</strong> IT Consultant  \n<strong>9.</strong> Opportunities locally or abroad  \n\n<strong>CAREER OPPORTUNITIES (BSCPE):</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Computer Hardware Engineer  \n<strong>2.</strong> Network Engineer  \n<strong>3.</strong> Telecommunications Engineer  \n<strong>4.</strong> Robotics Engineer  \n<strong>5.</strong> Systems Engineer  \n<strong>6.</strong> Embedded Systems Developer  \n<strong>7.</strong> Electronics Engineer  \n\n<strong>WHY CHOOSE TECH AT LCC:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Updated curriculum aligned with current technologies  \n<strong>2.</strong> Hands-on laboratory experience  \n<strong>3.</strong> Industry-standard software  \n<strong>4.</strong> Experienced IT faculty  \n<strong>5.</strong> High demand leading to strong job opportunities  \n\n<strong>SALARY POTENTIAL:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Entry Level: ₱20,000 to ₱35,000 per month  \n<strong>2.</strong> Experienced: ₱50,000 to ₱150,000+ per month  \n<strong>3.</strong> Abroad: $4,000 to $10,000+ per month  \n\n<strong>TECH INDUSTRY DEMAND:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> High demand for skilled professionals  \n<strong>2.</strong> Opportunities to work globally  \n<strong>3.</strong> Competitive salary and benefits  \n<strong>4.</strong> Strong career growth opportunities  \n\n<strong>NEXT STEPS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Ask about admission requirements  \n<strong>2.</strong> Ask about tuition fees for Computer Science or Computer Engineering  \n<strong>3.</strong> Ask about the differences between BSCS and BSCPE  \n\nThe future is in technology, and it starts here.	about_computer_science	70.49021771861835	2026-03-30 13:46:21.078088+08	\N
714	what is acamic scholarship	Excellent! Let me tell you about our Academic Scholarship Program!\n\n<strong>WHAT IS IT:</strong>  \nThe Academic Scholarship is awarded to students who are among the <strong>top five (5)</strong> of their graduating batch or class based on their general average.\n<strong>WHO CAN QUALIFY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Top 1 (Valedictorian)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Top 2 (Salutatorian)  \n<strong>3.</strong> Top 3  \n<strong>4.</strong> Top 4  \n<strong>5.</strong> Top 5  \n\n<strong>SCHOLARSHIP BENEFITS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Rank 1 - 100% discount on tuition and miscellaneous fees  \n<strong>2.</strong> Rank 2 - 75% discount on tuition and miscellaneous fees  \n<strong>3.</strong> Rank 3 - 50% discount on tuition and miscellaneous fees  \n<strong>4.</strong> Rank 4 - 30% discount on tuition and miscellaneous fees  \n<strong>5.</strong> Rank 5 - 20% discount on tuition and miscellaneous fees  \n\n<strong>DURATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Renewable until program completion, provided requirements are maintained  \n\n<strong>HOW TO MAINTAIN THE SCHOLARSHIP:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> No grades lower than 2.25 in any subject  \n<strong>2.</strong> Maintain a GPA of 1.75 or higher  \n<strong>3.</strong> Remain in good standing with no disciplinary actions  \n<strong>4.</strong> Submit a certified true copy of your latest grades  \n\n<strong>RENEWAL BENEFITS (BASED ON GPA):</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> GPA 1.00 to 1.25 - 100% discount  \n<strong>2.</strong> GPA 1.26 to 1.50 - 75% discount  \n<strong>3.</strong> GPA 1.51 to 1.75 - 50% discount  \n\n<strong>REQUIREMENTS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Certified true copy of latest grades (Form 138)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Proof of ranking (Top 1 to 5)  \n\n<strong>WHERE TO APPLY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Scholarships Office or Marketing Office  \n\n<strong>PRO TIP:</strong>  \nThis scholarship covers both tuition and miscellaneous fees, making it more comprehensive than many other scholarship programs.\n\nCongratulations on your academic achievement! Would you like to know about admission requirements or the enrollment process?	about_academic_scholarship	73.90396004905291	2026-03-30 13:47:01.192421+08	\N
715	what is pnp discount	Of course! Let me tell you about the PNP Discount!\n\n<strong>WHAT IS IT:</strong>  \nThis is a special discount for students whose parent is a member of the Philippine National Police (PNP), regardless of rank or position.\n\n<strong>WHO CAN QUALIFY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Parent is an active PNP member  \n<strong>2.</strong> Applies to any rank or position  \n\n<strong>BENEFITS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> 20% discount on tuition fee  \n\n<strong>WHAT IT COVERS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Tuition fee only  \n<strong>2.</strong> Does not include miscellaneous fees  \n\n<strong>DURATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Renewable until program completion  \n\n<strong>HOW TO MAINTAIN THE DISCOUNT:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> No failing grades  \n<strong>2.</strong> Maintain good standing with no disciplinary records  \n<strong>3.</strong> Submit certified true copy of latest grades  \n\n<strong>REQUIREMENTS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Proof of parent’s PNP membership (PNP ID or Certificate of Employment)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Latest grades (Form 138)  \n<strong>3.</strong> Scholarship application form  \n\n<strong>WHERE TO APPLY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Marketing Office  \n<strong>2.</strong> Scholarships Office  \n\n<strong>CAN YOU COMBINE WITH OTHER SCHOLARSHIPS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Only one institutional discount is allowed at a time  \n<strong>2.</strong> Can be combined with government or external scholarships  \n\n<strong>EXAMPLE SAVINGS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> If tuition is ₱20,000, a 20% discount reduces it to ₱16,000  \n<strong>2.</strong> Savings of ₱4,000 per semester  \n\n<strong>NOTE:</strong>  \nThis program recognizes and supports families of PNP personnel.\n\nWould you like to know about other discounts or scholarship options? Just ask!	about_pnp_discount	70.12357225190226	2026-03-30 13:47:55.840838+08	\N
