717	what is solo parent discount	Of course! Let me explain the Solo Parent Discount!\n\n<strong>WHAT IS IT:</strong>  \nThis is a special discount for students whose parent is a solo parent.\n\n<strong>WHO CAN QUALIFY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Parent is widowed  \n<strong>2.</strong> Parent is legally separated or divorced  \n<strong>3.</strong> Parent is unmarried or a single parent  \n\n<strong>BENEFITS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> 20% discount on tuition fee  \n\n<strong>WHAT IT COVERS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Tuition fee only  \n<strong>2.</strong> Does not include miscellaneous fees  \n\n<strong>DURATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Renewable until program completion  \n\n<strong>HOW TO MAINTAIN THE DISCOUNT:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> No failing grades  \n<strong>2.</strong> Maintain good standing with no disciplinary records  \n<strong>3.</strong> Submit certified true copy of latest grades  \n\n<strong>REQUIREMENTS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Solo Parent ID issued by the local government  \n<strong>2.</strong> Latest grades (Form 138)  \n<strong>3.</strong> Scholarship application form  \n\n<strong>HOW TO GET A SOLO PARENT ID:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Visit the City or Municipal Social Welfare Office  \n<strong>2.</strong> Provide proof of solo parent status:  \n   • Death certificate (if widowed)  \n   • Legal documents for separation or annulment  \n   • Affidavit (if unmarried)  \n<strong>3.</strong> Processing may take a few days  \n\n<strong>WHERE TO APPLY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Marketing Office  \n<strong>2.</strong> Scholarships Office  \n\n<strong>CAN YOU COMBINE WITH OTHER SCHOLARSHIPS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Only one institutional discount is allowed at a time  \n<strong>2.</strong> Can be combined with government scholarships  \n\n<strong>EXAMPLE SAVINGS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> If tuition is ₱20,000, a 20% discount reduces it to ₱16,000  \n<strong>2.</strong> Savings of ₱4,000 per semester  \n<strong>3.</strong> Total savings over 4 years can reach ₱32,000  \n\n<strong>OTHER AVAILABLE DISCOUNTS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Alumni Discount  \n<strong>2.</strong> PNP Discount  \n<strong>3.</strong> PWD Discount  \n<strong>4.</strong> Family Privilege Discount  \n\n<strong>NOTE:</strong>  \nThis program supports families by helping reduce the financial burden of education.\n\nNeed help with the application process or payment options? Just ask!	about_solo_parent_discount	70.1328323692111	2026-03-30 13:48:42.527752+08	\N
718	how long is nursing	Excellent choice! Let me tell you all about our Nursing program!\n\n<strong>WHAT IS IT?</strong>  \nBachelor of Science in Nursing is a 4-year healthcare program that prepares you to become a professional registered nurse. You will learn to provide patient care, promote health, and work in hospitals, clinics, and other healthcare facilities.\n\n<strong>PROGRAM HIGHLIGHTS:</strong>  \n<strong>DURATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> 4 years (8 semesters)  \n\n<strong>WHAT YOU WILL STUDY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Anatomy and Physiology  \n<strong>2.</strong> Pharmacology (medicines and drugs)  \n<strong>3.</strong> Medical-Surgical Nursing  \n<strong>4.</strong> Maternal and Child Health Nursing  \n<strong>5.</strong> Community Health Nursing  \n<strong>6.</strong> Mental Health Nursing  \n<strong>7.</strong> Clinical practice and hospital duty  \n\n<strong>HANDS-ON TRAINING:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Clinical rotations in real hospitals  \n<strong>2.</strong> Simulation laboratories with medical equipment  \n<strong>3.</strong> Patient care experience  \n<strong>4.</strong> Skills training and practice  \n\n<strong>AFTER GRADUATION:</strong>  \n\n<strong>LICENSURE EXAM:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Take the Nurse Licensure Examination (NLE) conducted by PRC  \n<strong>2.</strong> Passing the exam allows you to become a Registered Nurse (RN)  \n\n<strong>CAREER OPPORTUNITIES:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Hospital Nurse (Staff Nurse, Charge Nurse, Head Nurse)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Overseas Nurse (USA, UK, Canada, Middle East)  \n<strong>3.</strong> Nurse Educator or Professor  \n<strong>4.</strong> Occupational Health Nurse  \n<strong>5.</strong> Public Health Nurse  \n<strong>6.</strong> Clinical Specialist  \n<strong>7.</strong> Healthcare Management  \n\n<strong>WHY CHOOSE NURSING AT LCC:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Well-equipped nursing laboratories  \n<strong>2.</strong> Experienced faculty members  \n<strong>3.</strong> Hospital affiliations for clinical duty  \n<strong>4.</strong> Strong board exam performance  \n<strong>5.</strong> Many graduates working abroad  \n\n<strong>SALARY POTENTIAL:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Philippines: ₱15,000 to ₱30,000+ per month (starting)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Abroad: $3,000 to $8,000+ per month  \n\n<strong>NEXT STEPS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Ask about admission requirements for Nursing  \n<strong>2.</strong> Ask about tuition fees for Nursing  \n<strong>3.</strong> Ask about enrollment schedule  \n\nNursing is a rewarding career with excellent opportunities both locally and internationally!	about_nursing	69.41780967114391	2026-03-30 13:49:50.033949+08	\N
