751	What are the admission requirements?	Great! I'm excited to help you understand how to apply! The process is pretty straightforward. Let me walk you through it step by step!\n\n<strong>IF YOU'RE A NEW STUDENT (First time at LCC):</strong>\n<strong>1. Fill out the online application form</strong>\nVisit: http://lcc-silvercrest.com and complete the form\n<strong>2. Wait for approval</strong>\nThe Guidance & Admission Office will review your application\n<strong>3. Attend the admission interview</strong>\nYou'll be invited for a short interview at the Guidance & Admission Office\n<strong>4. Receive your Admission Slip</strong>\nOnce approved, you'll get your admission slip\n<strong>5. Visit your program's department office</strong>\nGo to the specific office for your chosen course\n<strong>6. Complete enrollment</strong>\nProceed with assessment and payment at the Cashier\n\n<strong>IF YOU'RE A RETURNING STUDENT:</strong>\n1. Fill out the pre-registration form\n2. Get it approved by your Dean\n3. Go to the Registrar's office for encoding\n4. Pay at the Cashier's Office\n5. Exchange your old ID for a new one\n\nDon't worry - the staff will guide you at every step. Would you like to know what documents you need to prepare? Or do you have questions about enrollment schedules? I'm here to help!	admission_procedure	72.52862556503415	2026-03-30 15:14:13.676365+08	\N
752	do you offer nursing?	Yes, we offer <strong>Bachelor of Science in Nursing (BSN)</strong>.\n\n<strong>PROGRAM:</strong> BS Nursing (BSN) - 4-year healthcare program\n<strong>COLLEGE:</strong> College of Nursing\n<strong>DURATION:</strong> 4 years\n\n<strong>You can ask about:</strong>\n<strong>1.</strong> Curriculum and subjects\n<strong>2.</strong> Career opportunities\n<strong>3.</strong> Admission requirements\n<strong>4.</strong> Tuition fees\n\nJust ask and I will be happy to help.	program_entity_single_BSN	95	2026-03-30 15:14:23.793489+08	\N
753	Tell me more about the subjects	Great question! I'd love to tell you what you'll learn!\n\nThe subjects depend on which program you choose. Each program has its own specialized curriculum designed to prepare you for your career.\n\n<strong>General Education subjects (all programs):</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> English, Filipino, Mathematics, and Science  \n<strong>2.</strong> Social Sciences and Humanities  \n<strong>3.</strong> Computer basics and Research methods  \n\n<strong>Program-specific subjects vary depending on your chosen course.</strong>\n\n<strong>For detailed curriculum of a specific program:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Contact the <strong>department office</strong> of your chosen course  \n<strong>2.</strong> Visit our website at https://www.lipacitycolleges.edu.ph/  \n<strong>3.</strong> Ask during your campus visit  \n<strong>4.</strong> Talk to our admission counselors\n\nDo you more question? Just ask! 	program_subjects	69.60400645376514	2026-03-30 15:14:37.856604+08	\N
