755	Tell me about Nursing	Excellent choice! Let me tell you all about our Nursing program!\n\n<strong>WHAT IS IT?</strong>  \nBachelor of Science in Nursing is a 4-year healthcare program that prepares you to become a professional registered nurse. You will learn to provide patient care, promote health, and work in hospitals, clinics, and other healthcare facilities.\n\n<strong>PROGRAM HIGHLIGHTS:</strong>  \n<strong>DURATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> 4 years (8 semesters)  \n\n<strong>WHAT YOU WILL STUDY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Anatomy and Physiology  \n<strong>2.</strong> Pharmacology (medicines and drugs)  \n<strong>3.</strong> Medical-Surgical Nursing  \n<strong>4.</strong> Maternal and Child Health Nursing  \n<strong>5.</strong> Community Health Nursing  \n<strong>6.</strong> Mental Health Nursing  \n<strong>7.</strong> Clinical practice and hospital duty  \n\n<strong>HANDS-ON TRAINING:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Clinical rotations in real hospitals  \n<strong>2.</strong> Simulation laboratories with medical equipment  \n<strong>3.</strong> Patient care experience  \n<strong>4.</strong> Skills training and practice  \n\n<strong>AFTER GRADUATION:</strong>  \n\n<strong>LICENSURE EXAM:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Take the Nurse Licensure Examination (NLE) conducted by PRC  \n<strong>2.</strong> Passing the exam allows you to become a Registered Nurse (RN)  \n\n<strong>CAREER OPPORTUNITIES:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Hospital Nurse (Staff Nurse, Charge Nurse, Head Nurse)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Overseas Nurse (USA, UK, Canada, Middle East)  \n<strong>3.</strong> Nurse Educator or Professor  \n<strong>4.</strong> Occupational Health Nurse  \n<strong>5.</strong> Public Health Nurse  \n<strong>6.</strong> Clinical Specialist  \n<strong>7.</strong> Healthcare Management  \n\n<strong>WHY CHOOSE NURSING AT LCC:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Well-equipped nursing laboratories  \n<strong>2.</strong> Experienced faculty members  \n<strong>3.</strong> Hospital affiliations for clinical duty  \n<strong>4.</strong> Strong board exam performance  \n<strong>5.</strong> Many graduates working abroad  \n\n<strong>SALARY POTENTIAL:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Philippines: ₱15,000 to ₱30,000+ per month (starting)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Abroad: $3,000 to $8,000+ per month  \n\n<strong>NEXT STEPS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Ask about admission requirements for Nursing  \n<strong>2.</strong> Ask about tuition fees for Nursing  \n<strong>3.</strong> Ask about enrollment schedule  \n\nNursing is a rewarding career with excellent opportunities both locally and internationally!	about_nursing	69.49784914678116	2026-03-30 15:17:25.786458+08	\N
756	What jobs can I get after Nursing?	Excellent question about career opportunities! Let me tell you about the exciting paths our graduates take!\n\n<strong>Our graduates have many career options depending on their program:</strong>\n<strong>BUSINESS AND ACCOUNTANCY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Corporate jobs, banking, finance, marketing, human resources, entrepreneurship  \n<strong>2.</strong> Accounting firms, auditing, tax consultancy  \n<strong>3.</strong> International opportunities in various industries  \n\n<strong>EDUCATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Public and private school teachers  \n<strong>2.</strong> Tutorial centers and review centers  \n<strong>3.</strong> Teaching opportunities abroad  \n\n<strong>NURSING:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Hospitals (local and international)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Clinics and healthcare facilities  \n<strong>3.</strong> Opportunities to work abroad  \n\n<strong>CRIMINOLOGY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Police, NBI, and other law enforcement agencies  \n<strong>2.</strong> Private investigation and security management  \n<strong>3.</strong> Government service roles  \n\n<strong>COMPUTER SCIENCE AND ENGINEERING:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Software developer or programmer  \n<strong>2.</strong> IT consultant or systems analyst  \n<strong>3.</strong> Careers in tech companies (local and international)  \n\n<strong>HOSPITALITY AND TOURISM:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Hotels, resorts, and restaurants  \n<strong>2.</strong> Airlines and travel agencies  \n<strong>3.</strong> Event management  \n\n<strong>Many of our graduates also pursue:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Graduate studies (Master’s or Doctorate degrees)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Government positions  \n<strong>3.</strong> Entrepreneurship  \n\nWhich program interests you? I can give you more specific career information!	program_career_prospects	69.94472608107849	2026-03-30 15:17:37.637511+08	\N
