780	Performing arts scholarship LCC	Great question for our artists and performers! Let me tell you about the Cultural Scholarship!\n\n<strong>WHAT IS IT:</strong>  \nThe Cultural Scholarship is awarded to students who demonstrate strong talent in the performing arts and represent LCC in cultural events and competitions.\n\n<strong>WHO CAN QUALIFY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Students with exceptional performing arts skills  \n<strong>2.</strong> Students who represent or qualify to represent LCC in cultural activities  \n<strong>3.</strong> May include dancers, singers, musicians, theater performers, and others  \n<strong>4.</strong> Must maintain both academic and cultural participation requirements  \n\n<strong>BENEFITS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Tuition fee discount based on performance evaluation  \n\n<strong>HOW TO APPLY OR BE CONSIDERED:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Contact the Cultural Organizations or Student Affairs Office  \n<strong>2.</strong> Participate in auditions or performance evaluations  \n<strong>3.</strong> Submit required documents  \n\n<strong>WHERE TO APPLY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Cultural Organizations Section or Student Affairs Office  \n<strong>2.</strong> Scholarships Office for processing  \n\n<strong>IMPORTANT NOTES:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Details on cultural groups, audition schedules, and discount rates may vary  \n<strong>2.</strong> Refer to the Student Handbook or contact the office directly for updated information  \n\n<strong>CULTURAL GROUPS MAY INCLUDE:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Dance troupe  \n<strong>2.</strong> Choir or singing groups  \n<strong>3.</strong> Theater or drama club  \n<strong>4.</strong> Band or musical ensemble  \n<strong>5.</strong> Other performing arts groups  \n\n<strong>HOW TO MAINTAIN THE SCHOLARSHIP:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Maintain required academic performance  \n<strong>2.</strong> Actively participate in cultural groups and events  \n<strong>3.</strong> Maintain good standing with no disciplinary records  \n<strong>4.</strong> Represent LCC in performances and competitions as required  \n\n<strong>NOTE:</strong>  \nThis scholarship allows students to develop their artistic talents while receiving educational support.\n\nFor complete and updated details, visit the Scholarships Office or Student Affairs Office.\n\nWould you like to know about other scholarships available? Just ask!	about_cultural_scholarship	70.78823261246816	2026-03-30 15:47:26.340916+08	\N
781	Library	Sure! Here's when you can visit our library!\n\n<strong>Library Hours:</strong>\n<strong>1.</strong> Monday to Saturday: <strong>8:00 AM to 5:00 PM</strong>  \n<strong>2.</strong> Closed on Sundays and holidays  \n\nThat's 9 hours a day to study, research, or borrow books! The library staff are very helpful too - they can assist you in finding references for your projects.\n\nDo you have any other questions? Maybe about our programs, admission requirements, or enrollment? I'm here to help!	library_hours	77.77658670228868	2026-03-30 15:48:07.323525+08	\N
