786	[Clicked: Information about Business and Accountancy programs]	Excellent choice! Let me tell you about our Business programs!\n\n<strong>YES, WE OFFER THREE BUSINESS PROGRAMS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> <strong>Bachelor of Science in Business Administration (BSBA)</strong>  \n<strong>2.</strong> <strong>Bachelor of Science in Accountancy (BSA)</strong>  \n<strong>3.</strong> <strong>Bachelor of Science in Management Accounting (BSMA)</strong>  \n\n<strong>PROGRAM DETAILS:</strong>  \n<strong>DURATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> All programs take 4 years (8 semesters)  \n\n<strong>BSBA - BUSINESS ADMINISTRATION:</strong>  \n<strong>CHOOSE YOUR MAJOR:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Marketing - Sales, advertising, and brand management  \n<strong>2.</strong> Human Resource Management - Recruitment and people management  \n<strong>3.</strong> Financial Management - Investments and corporate finance  \n\n<strong>WHAT YOU WILL STUDY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Management and Organization  \n<strong>2.</strong> Marketing Principles  \n<strong>3.</strong> Financial Management  \n<strong>4.</strong> Accounting basics  \n<strong>5.</strong> Business Law  \n<strong>6.</strong> Operations Management  \n<strong>7.</strong> Entrepreneurship  \n<strong>8.</strong> Business Analytics  \n\n<strong>CAREER OPPORTUNITIES:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Marketing or Sales Manager  \n<strong>2.</strong> Human Resource Manager or Recruitment Specialist  \n<strong>3.</strong> Financial Analyst  \n<strong>4.</strong> Business Operations Manager  \n<strong>5.</strong> Business Development Officer  \n<strong>6.</strong> Entrepreneur or Business Owner  \n<strong>7.</strong> Export or Import Manager  \n\n<strong>BSA - ACCOUNTANCY:</strong>  \n<strong>PREPARE TO BECOME A CPA:</strong>  \n\n<strong>WHAT YOU WILL STUDY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Financial Accounting  \n<strong>2.</strong> Auditing  \n<strong>3.</strong> Cost Accounting  \n<strong>4.</strong> Tax Accounting  \n<strong>5.</strong> Management Advisory Services  \n<strong>6.</strong> Accounting Information Systems  \n<strong>7.</strong> Business Law  \n\n<strong>AFTER GRADUATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Take the CPA Licensure Examination  \n<strong>2.</strong> Become a Certified Public Accountant  \n\n<strong>CAREER OPPORTUNITIES:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Public Accountant (audit firms)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Corporate Accountant  \n<strong>3.</strong> Tax Consultant  \n<strong>4.</strong> Internal Auditor  \n<strong>5.</strong> Financial Analyst  \n<strong>6.</strong> Chief Financial Officer  \n<strong>7.</strong> Government Accountant  \n<strong>8.</strong> Accounting Professor  \n\n<strong>BSMA - MANAGEMENT ACCOUNTING:</strong>  \n<strong>COMBINES ACCOUNTING AND BUSINESS MANAGEMENT:</strong>  \n\n<strong>WHAT YOU WILL STUDY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Accounting principles  \n<strong>2.</strong> Management concepts  \n<strong>3.</strong> Strategic planning  \n<strong>4.</strong> Cost management  \n<strong>5.</strong> Business analytics  \n\n<strong>CAREER OPPORTUNITIES:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Management Accountant  \n<strong>2.</strong> Financial Controller  \n<strong>3.</strong> Budget Analyst  \n<strong>4.</strong> Corporate Finance Manager  \n<strong>5.</strong> Business Consultant  \n\n<strong>WHY CHOOSE BUSINESS AT LCC:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Strong business curriculum  \n<strong>2.</strong> Experienced faculty members  \n<strong>3.</strong> Industry connections  \n<strong>4.</strong> Entrepreneurship support  \n<strong>5.</strong> Good board exam performance for BSA  \n<strong>6.</strong> Job placement assistance  \n\n<strong>SALARY POTENTIAL:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> BSBA Entry Level: ₱18,000 to ₱30,000 per month  \n<strong>2.</strong> BSA or CPA: ₱25,000 to ₱80,000+ per month  \n<strong>3.</strong> BSMA: ₱20,000 to ₱60,000+ per month  \n<strong>4.</strong> Abroad: $2,500 to $8,000+ per month  \n\n<strong>WHICH PROGRAM TO CHOOSE:</strong>  \n\n<strong>CHOOSE BSBA IF:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> You are interested in marketing, sales, or people management  \n<strong>2.</strong> You want flexibility with different majors  \n<strong>3.</strong> You want to start your own business  \n\n<strong>CHOOSE BSA IF:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> You are strong in mathematics and analysis  \n<strong>2.</strong> You want to become a CPA  \n<strong>3.</strong> You prefer detailed and structured work  \n<strong>4.</strong> You want to work in audit firms  \n\n<strong>CHOOSE BSMA IF:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> You want both accounting and management skills  \n<strong>2.</strong> You are interested in corporate finance  \n<strong>3.</strong> You enjoy business strategy and analysis  \n\n<strong>NEXT STEPS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Ask about admission requirements  \n<strong>2.</strong> Ask about tuition fees for Business programs  \n<strong>3.</strong> Ask about differences between BSBA, BSA, and BSMA  \n\nBusiness skills are always in demand and open many career opportunities.	about_business_programs	100	2026-03-30 15:54:42.854988+08	\N
787	courses available?	Awesome! Let me share all the programs we offer here at Lipa City Colleges!\n\n<strong>COLLEGE OF EDUCATION AND LIBERAL ARTS:</strong>\n<strong>1.</strong> Elementary Education (BEED) - Perfect if you want to teach young kids  \n<strong>2.</strong> Secondary Education (BSED) - Major in English, Math, Filipino, or Science  \n<strong>3.</strong> Psychology (AB-PSY) - Understand how the mind works  \n\n<strong>COLLEGE OF BUSINESS AND ACCOUNTANCY:</strong>\n<strong>1.</strong> Business Administration (BSBA) - Choose from Marketing, HR, or Financial Management  \n<strong>2.</strong> Accountancy (BSA) - For future CPAs  \n<strong>3.</strong> Management Accounting (BSMA) - Combine business and accounting  \n\n<strong>COLLEGE OF COMPUTING AND TECHNOLOGY ENGINEERING:</strong>\n<strong>1.</strong> Computer Science (BSCS) - Software development and programming  \n<strong>2.</strong> Computer Engineering (BSCPE) - Hardware and software combined  \n\n<strong>COLLEGE OF NURSING:</strong>\n<strong>1.</strong> Nursing (BSN) - Join the healthcare field  \n\n<strong>COLLEGE OF CRIMINAL JUSTICE EDUCATION:</strong>\n<strong>1.</strong> Criminology (BSCRIM) - Prepare for law enforcement careers  \n\n<strong>COLLEGE OF INTERNATIONAL TOURISM AND HOSPITALITY:</strong>\n<strong>1.</strong> Hospitality Management (BSHM) - Hotels, restaurants, and events  \n<strong>2.</strong> Tourism Management (BSTM) - Travel and tourism industry  \n\nWhich program interests you? I can tell you more about specific courses or help with admission requirements if you would like.	list_of_academic_programs	69.63463575928267	2026-03-30 15:57:58.844104+08	\N
788	[Clicked: Subjects and curriculum of programs]	Great question! I'd love to tell you what you'll learn!\n\nThe subjects depend on which program you choose. Each program has its own specialized curriculum designed to prepare you for your career.\n\n<strong>General Education subjects (all programs):</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> English, Filipino, Mathematics, and Science  \n<strong>2.</strong> Social Sciences and Humanities  \n<strong>3.</strong> Computer basics and Research methods  \n\n<strong>Program-specific subjects vary depending on your chosen course.</strong>\n\n<strong>For detailed curriculum of a specific program:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Contact the <strong>department office</strong> of your chosen course  \n<strong>2.</strong> Visit our website at https://www.lipacitycolleges.edu.ph/  \n<strong>3.</strong> Ask during your campus visit  \n<strong>4.</strong> Talk to our admission counselors\n\nDo you more question? Just ask! 	program_subjects	100	2026-03-30 15:58:25.289203+08	\N
