796	Total fees	I understand that tuition fees are an important consideration for families!\nThe tuition fees at Lipa City Colleges <strong>vary depending on your program and year level</strong>. For example, programs like Nursing or Engineering might have different fees compared to Business or Education courses due to laboratory requirements and specialized equipment.\n\n<strong>For specific tuition rates, I recommend:</strong>\n<strong>1.</strong> Visiting the <strong>Cashier's Office</strong> - they have the complete breakdown  \n<strong>2.</strong> Calling the <strong>Admissions Office</strong> - they can give you detailed information  \n<strong>3.</strong> Checking with the <strong>department office</strong> of your chosen program  \n\n<strong>Good news!</strong> We also have <strong>scholarship programs</strong> that can help reduce your tuition. Some students get 25% to 100% discounts through our Academic Scholarship, and we have other grants too.\n\nWould you like to know more about our scholarship programs? They might help make your education more affordable!	tuition_fees	68.51523565897865	2026-03-30 16:26:16.04214+08	\N
797	Available scholarships	<strong>INSTITUTIONAL SCHOLARSHIPS (FROM THE SCHOOL):</strong>  \n\n<strong>1.</strong> <strong>Academic Scholarship</strong> - Get 25% to 100% discount based on your grades. Higher GPA means higher discount  \n<strong>2.</strong> <strong>Gawad Karunungan</strong> - Full scholarship for outstanding students  \n<strong>3.</strong> <strong>Carlos R. Mojares Leadership Scholarship</strong> - Full tuition discount for student leaders  \n<strong>4.</strong> <strong>Family Privilege</strong> - Discounts for families with multiple enrolled members  \n<strong>5.</strong> <strong>Solo Parent Discount</strong> - 20% tuition discount for students with solo parents  \n<strong>6.</strong> <strong>Alumni Discount</strong> - 20% tuition discount if a parent graduated from LCC  \n<strong>7.</strong> <strong>AYOUDA Program</strong> - 50% tuition discount for students from distant areas  \n<strong>8.</strong> <strong>BEAP</strong> - 50% tuition discount for students affected by the Taal eruption  \n\n<strong>GOVERNMENT SCHOLARSHIPS:</strong>  \n\n<strong>1.</strong> <strong>Mayor Eric B. Africa (EBA) Scholarship</strong> - For qualified Lipa City residents  \n<strong>2.</strong> <strong>Provincial Capitol Scholarship</strong> - Assistance from the provincial government  \n<strong>3.</strong> <strong>CHED Scholarships</strong> - National-level scholarship programs  \n\n<strong>HOW TO APPLY:</strong>  \n\n<strong>1.</strong> Visit the Marketing Office and submit your application  \n<strong>2.</strong> Follow the guidance provided by the staff  \n\nFor specific requirements, deadlines, or to find the best scholarship for you, you may also visit the Student Affairs Office or the Guidance and Admission Office.\n\nWould you like to know more about admission requirements or the enrollment process? I'm here to help!	scholarship_programs	69.35836308814665	2026-03-30 16:26:26.540473+08	\N
798	How do I apply?	I'm glad you're interested in our scholarships! Let me guide you through the application process!\n\n<strong>STEP-BY-STEP APPLICATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> <strong>Visit the Marketing Office</strong>  \nLocated on campus  \nOffice hours: Monday to Saturday, 8:00 AM to 5:00 PM  \n\n<strong>2.</strong> <strong>Submit requirements</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Scholarship application form (available at the Marketing Office)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Form 138 (for academic scholarships)  \n<strong>3.</strong> Supporting documents depending on scholarship type:  \n   • Solo Parent ID (for Solo Parent Discount)  \n   • Parent's Alumni Certificate (for Alumni Discount)  \n   • Barangay Certificate (for some programs)  \n   • etc.  \n\n<strong>3.</strong> <strong>Wait for evaluation</strong>  \nThe office reviews your application  \nProcessing time usually takes a few days to one week  \n\n<strong>4.</strong> <strong>Receive approval</strong>  \nIf approved, you will be notified  \nYou will receive a scholarship grant letter  \n\n<strong>5.</strong> <strong>Proceed with enrollment</strong>  \nThe scholarship discount will be applied during enrollment  \nIt will appear on your assessment form  \n\n<strong>DIFFERENT SCHOLARSHIPS, DIFFERENT PROCESSES:</strong>  \n\n<strong>ACADEMIC SCHOLARSHIP:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Automatic for qualifying GPA  \n<strong>2.</strong> Submit Form 138 showing grades  \n\n<strong>GOVERNMENT SCHOLARSHIPS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Apply directly to the government office (CHED, Mayor's Office, etc.)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Submit requirements to them first, then inform LCC  \n\n<strong>SPECIAL SCHOLARSHIPS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Submit proof of eligibility  \n<strong>2.</strong> May require an interview  \n\n<strong>IMPORTANT TIPS:</strong>  \n\n<strong>1.</strong> Apply early as some scholarships have limited slots  \n<strong>2.</strong> Apply before enrollment for better chances  \n<strong>3.</strong> Maintain good grades to keep your scholarship each semester  \n\n<strong>WHERE TO GO:</strong>  \n\n<strong>1.</strong> Marketing Office - Institutional scholarships  \n<strong>2.</strong> Student Affairs Office - Guidance on available scholarships  \n<strong>3.</strong> CHED or government offices - Government scholarships  \n\n<strong>MORE QUESTIONS?</strong>  \nWant to know which scholarship you qualify for? Just tell me your situation and I can suggest options!	scholarship_application_process	67.68444049163614	2026-03-30 16:26:38.715145+08	\N
799	how do I apply?	I'm glad you're interested in our scholarships! Let me guide you through the application process!\n\n<strong>STEP-BY-STEP APPLICATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> <strong>Visit the Marketing Office</strong>  \nLocated on campus  \nOffice hours: Monday to Saturday, 8:00 AM to 5:00 PM  \n\n<strong>2.</strong> <strong>Submit requirements</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Scholarship application form (available at the Marketing Office)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Form 138 (for academic scholarships)  \n<strong>3.</strong> Supporting documents depending on scholarship type:  \n   • Solo Parent ID (for Solo Parent Discount)  \n   • Parent's Alumni Certificate (for Alumni Discount)  \n   • Barangay Certificate (for some programs)  \n   • etc.  \n\n<strong>3.</strong> <strong>Wait for evaluation</strong>  \nThe office reviews your application  \nProcessing time usually takes a few days to one week  \n\n<strong>4.</strong> <strong>Receive approval</strong>  \nIf approved, you will be notified  \nYou will receive a scholarship grant letter  \n\n<strong>5.</strong> <strong>Proceed with enrollment</strong>  \nThe scholarship discount will be applied during enrollment  \nIt will appear on your assessment form  \n\n<strong>DIFFERENT SCHOLARSHIPS, DIFFERENT PROCESSES:</strong>  \n\n<strong>ACADEMIC SCHOLARSHIP:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Automatic for qualifying GPA  \n<strong>2.</strong> Submit Form 138 showing grades  \n\n<strong>GOVERNMENT SCHOLARSHIPS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Apply directly to the government office (CHED, Mayor's Office, etc.)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Submit requirements to them first, then inform LCC  \n\n<strong>SPECIAL SCHOLARSHIPS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Submit proof of eligibility  \n<strong>2.</strong> May require an interview  \n\n<strong>IMPORTANT TIPS:</strong>  \n\n<strong>1.</strong> Apply early as some scholarships have limited slots  \n<strong>2.</strong> Apply before enrollment for better chances  \n<strong>3.</strong> Maintain good grades to keep your scholarship each semester  \n\n<strong>WHERE TO GO:</strong>  \n\n<strong>1.</strong> Marketing Office - Institutional scholarships  \n<strong>2.</strong> Student Affairs Office - Guidance on available scholarships  \n<strong>3.</strong> CHED or government offices - Government scholarships  \n\n<strong>MORE QUESTIONS?</strong>  \nWant to know which scholarship you qualify for? Just tell me your situation and I can suggest options!	scholarship_application_process	67.68444049163614	2026-03-30 16:26:58.847075+08	\N
800	Top 5 scholarship	Excellent! Let me tell you about our Academic Scholarship Program!\n\n<strong>WHAT IS IT:</strong>  \nThe Academic Scholarship is awarded to students who are among the <strong>top five (5)</strong> of their graduating batch or class based on their general average.\n<strong>WHO CAN QUALIFY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Top 1 (Valedictorian)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Top 2 (Salutatorian)  \n<strong>3.</strong> Top 3  \n<strong>4.</strong> Top 4  \n<strong>5.</strong> Top 5  \n\n<strong>SCHOLARSHIP BENEFITS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Rank 1 - 100% discount on tuition and miscellaneous fees  \n<strong>2.</strong> Rank 2 - 75% discount on tuition and miscellaneous fees  \n<strong>3.</strong> Rank 3 - 50% discount on tuition and miscellaneous fees  \n<strong>4.</strong> Rank 4 - 30% discount on tuition and miscellaneous fees  \n<strong>5.</strong> Rank 5 - 20% discount on tuition and miscellaneous fees  \n\n<strong>DURATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Renewable until program completion, provided requirements are maintained  \n\n<strong>HOW TO MAINTAIN THE SCHOLARSHIP:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> No grades lower than 2.25 in any subject  \n<strong>2.</strong> Maintain a GPA of 1.75 or higher  \n<strong>3.</strong> Remain in good standing with no disciplinary actions  \n<strong>4.</strong> Submit a certified true copy of your latest grades  \n\n<strong>RENEWAL BENEFITS (BASED ON GPA):</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> GPA 1.00 to 1.25 - 100% discount  \n<strong>2.</strong> GPA 1.26 to 1.50 - 75% discount  \n<strong>3.</strong> GPA 1.51 to 1.75 - 50% discount  \n\n<strong>REQUIREMENTS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Certified true copy of latest grades (Form 138)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Proof of ranking (Top 1 to 5)  \n\n<strong>WHERE TO APPLY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Scholarships Office or Marketing Office  \n\n<strong>PRO TIP:</strong>  \nThis scholarship covers both tuition and miscellaneous fees, making it more comprehensive than many other scholarship programs.\n\nCongratulations on your academic achievement! Would you like to know about admission requirements or the enrollment process?	about_academic_scholarship	78.84663553085439	2026-03-30 16:29:59.857992+08	\N
801	how can I enroll?	Good news! I can help you with that!\n<strong>Enrollment for the 2nd Semester starts on January 6, 2026!</strong>\n\nMark your calendar! It's best to enroll early to get your preferred schedule and avoid the rush.\n\nHere's a quick tip: Try to complete your requirements ahead of time so you can enroll on the first day. That way, you'll have more slots to choose from.\n\nWould you like to know what documents you need to prepare? Or maybe you're curious about the admission procedure? I'm happy to help you get ready! Just ask!	ask_when_is_enrollment	70.0626187415885	2026-03-30 16:30:17.468843+08	\N
802	Application steps	Great! I'm excited to help you understand how to apply! The process is pretty straightforward. Let me walk you through it step by step!\n\n<strong>IF YOU'RE A NEW STUDENT (First time at LCC):</strong>\n<strong>1. Fill out the online application form</strong>\nVisit: http://lcc-silvercrest.com and complete the form\n<strong>2. Wait for approval</strong>\nThe Guidance & Admission Office will review your application\n<strong>3. Attend the admission interview</strong>\nYou'll be invited for a short interview at the Guidance & Admission Office\n<strong>4. Receive your Admission Slip</strong>\nOnce approved, you'll get your admission slip\n<strong>5. Visit your program's department office</strong>\nGo to the specific office for your chosen course\n<strong>6. Complete enrollment</strong>\nProceed with assessment and payment at the Cashier\n\n<strong>IF YOU'RE A RETURNING STUDENT:</strong>\n1. Fill out the pre-registration form\n2. Get it approved by your Dean\n3. Go to the Registrar's office for encoding\n4. Pay at the Cashier's Office\n5. Exchange your old ID for a new one\n\nDon't worry - the staff will guide you at every step. Would you like to know what documents you need to prepare? Or do you have questions about enrollment schedules? I'm here to help!	admission_procedure	73.6678302380513	2026-03-30 16:30:32.797437+08	\N
803	What to submit?	Perfect! Let me help you prepare the documents you'll need!\n\n<strong>IF YOU'RE AN INCOMING FRESHMAN (from senior high school):</strong>\n\nYou'll need to bring these:\n<strong>1.</strong> <strong>Form 138</strong> (your report card)\n<strong>2.</strong> <strong>Form 137</strong> (permanent record)\n<strong>3.</strong> <strong>Certificate of Good Moral Character</strong>\n<strong>4.</strong> <strong>PSA Birth Certificate</strong> (the original from PSA, not just a photocopy)\n<strong>5.</strong> <strong>Three 2x2 ID photos</strong> (recent, with white background)\n<strong>6.</strong> <strong>Program-specific requirements</strong> (some courses might need additional documents)\n\nYou'll also need to:\n<strong>1.</strong> <strong>Take the entrance examination</strong>\n<strong>2.</strong> <strong>Attend an admission interview</strong>\n\n<strong>IF YOU'RE A TRANSFEREE (from another school):</strong>\nBring these documents:\n<strong>1.</strong> <strong>Transcript of Records (TOR)</strong>\n<strong>2.</strong> <strong>Certificate of Eligibility to Transfer</strong> (if applicable)\n<strong>3.</strong> <strong>Certificate of Good Moral Character</strong>\n<strong>4.</strong> <strong>PSA Birth Certificate</strong>\n<strong>5.</strong> <strong>2-3 pieces of 2x2 ID photos</strong>\n\nDon't worry! The Registrar will help evaluate which of your previous courses are creditable here at LCC.\n\nDo you need help with anything else? Like the admission procedure or enrollment schedule? Just let me know!	admission_requirements	69.33479325314688	2026-03-30 16:30:49.685687+08	\N
804	What is TOR?	No problem! Let me explain these documents for you!\n\n<strong>FORM 138 - Report Card:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Your grades from senior high school  \n<strong>2.</strong> Shows subjects you took and your performance  \n<strong>3.</strong> Get it from your previous school's registrar  \n\n<strong>FORM 137 - Permanent Record:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Your complete academic history (elementary to senior high)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Includes awards, attendance, and conduct records  \n<strong>3.</strong> More detailed than Form 138  \n\n<strong>PSA BIRTH CERTIFICATE:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Official birth certificate from the Philippine Statistics Authority  \n<strong>2.</strong> Has security features (not just a local copy)  \n<strong>3.</strong> Get it from PSA outlets or online: https://www.psahelpline.ph/  \n<strong>4.</strong> Costs around ₱155 per copy  \n\n<strong>CERTIFICATE OF GOOD MORAL CHARACTER:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Certifies you had good behavior in your previous school  \n<strong>2.</strong> Get it from your school principal or guidance office  \n<strong>3.</strong> Usually free or with minimal fee  \n\n<strong>TRANSCRIPT OF RECORDS (TOR):</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Required for transferees - contains your grades from previous college  \n<strong>2.</strong> Get it from your previous college's registrar  \n<strong>3.</strong> May take 1 to 2 weeks to process  \n\n<strong>GOOD MORAL CHARACTER (FOR TRANSFEREES):</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Certifies you have no disciplinary issues  \n<strong>2.</strong> Required for transferees  \n\n<strong>WHERE TO GET THESE DOCUMENTS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Forms 137 and 138 - Your senior high school registrar  \n<strong>2.</strong> PSA Birth Certificate - PSA outlets or online  \n<strong>3.</strong> Good Moral Certificate - School principal or guidance office  \n<strong>4.</strong> TOR - Previous college registrar (for transferees)  \n\nNeed help with anything else about requirements? Just ask!	document_clarification	68.92429934906396	2026-03-30 16:31:12.376491+08	\N
805	Application steps	Great! I'm excited to help you understand how to apply! The process is pretty straightforward. Let me walk you through it step by step!\n\n<strong>IF YOU'RE A NEW STUDENT (First time at LCC):</strong>\n<strong>1. Fill out the online application form</strong>\nVisit: http://lcc-silvercrest.com and complete the form\n<strong>2. Wait for approval</strong>\nThe Guidance & Admission Office will review your application\n<strong>3. Attend the admission interview</strong>\nYou'll be invited for a short interview at the Guidance & Admission Office\n<strong>4. Receive your Admission Slip</strong>\nOnce approved, you'll get your admission slip\n<strong>5. Visit your program's department office</strong>\nGo to the specific office for your chosen course\n<strong>6. Complete enrollment</strong>\nProceed with assessment and payment at the Cashier\n\n<strong>IF YOU'RE A RETURNING STUDENT:</strong>\n1. Fill out the pre-registration form\n2. Get it approved by your Dean\n3. Go to the Registrar's office for encoding\n4. Pay at the Cashier's Office\n5. Exchange your old ID for a new one\n\nDon't worry - the staff will guide you at every step. Would you like to know what documents you need to prepare? Or do you have questions about enrollment schedules? I'm here to help!	admission_procedure	73.6678302380513	2026-03-30 16:32:32.223741+08	\N
806	Where is the Library?	Library is located at 3rd Floor, RBB1.	ask_room_location	100	2026-03-30 17:58:35.193912+08	\N
807	library hours?	Sure! Here's when you can visit our library!\n\n<strong>Library Hours:</strong>\n<strong>1.</strong> Monday to Saturday: <strong>8:00 AM to 5:00 PM</strong>  \n<strong>2.</strong> Closed on Sundays and holidays  \n\nThat's 9 hours a day to study, research, or borrow books! The library staff are very helpful too - they can assist you in finding references for your projects.\n\nDo you have any other questions? Maybe about our programs, admission requirements, or enrollment? I'm here to help!	library_hours	69.78502967727024	2026-03-30 17:58:45.240322+08	\N
808	LCC official site	Hi there! I'd be happy to share our official website with you! 😊\r\n\r\nYou can visit us online at:\r\nWebsite: https://www.lipacitycolleges.edu.ph/\r\nFacebook: https://www.facebook.com/LeadershipCompetenceCommitment\r\n\r\nFeel free to explore our website to learn more about our programs, facilities, and campus life! If you have any other questions about admissions, scholarships, or our courses, just ask - I'm here to help!	official_website	70.31438582022055	2026-03-30 17:58:55.671149+08	\N
809	Campus features?	Great question! Let me give you a tour of our campus facilities!\n\n<strong>ACADEMIC FACILITIES:</strong>  \n<strong>LIBRARY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Reference books, periodicals, and electronic resources  \n<strong>2.</strong> Computer stations with internet access  \n<strong>3.</strong> Study areas and reading rooms  \n<strong>4.</strong> Open Monday to Saturday, 8:00 AM to 5:00 PM  \n\n<strong>COMPUTER LABORATORIES:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Modern computers with updated software  \n<strong>2.</strong> High-speed internet connection  \n<strong>3.</strong> Air-conditioned rooms  \n\n<strong>SCIENCE LABORATORIES:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Physics, Chemistry, and Biology laboratories  \n<strong>2.</strong> Equipped for experiments  \n<strong>3.</strong> Modern laboratory equipment  \n\n<strong>SPECIALIZED FACILITIES:</strong>  \n\n<strong>NURSING LABORATORIES:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Simulation laboratories for nursing students  \n<strong>2.</strong> Medical equipment and supplies  \n<strong>3.</strong> Skills training areas  \n\n<strong>CRIMINOLOGY TRAINING FACILITIES:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Physical fitness areas  \n<strong>2.</strong> Law enforcement training facilities  \n\n<strong>HOSPITALITY AND CULINARY LABORATORIES:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Kitchen facilities for BSHM students  \n<strong>2.</strong> Restaurant simulation areas  \n\n<strong>STUDENT AMENITIES:</strong>  \n\n<strong>CAFETERIA OR CANTEEN:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Affordable meals and snacks  \n<strong>2.</strong> Various food options  \n<strong>3.</strong> Student lounge area  \n\n<strong>CHAPEL:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Space for spiritual activities  \n<strong>2.</strong> Mass and prayer services  \n\n<strong>SPORTS FACILITIES:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Basketball court  \n<strong>2.</strong> Covered court for events  \n<strong>3.</strong> Physical education areas  \n\n<strong>ADMINISTRATIVE OFFICES:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Registrar, Cashier, and Guidance offices  \n<strong>2.</strong> Student Affairs and Marketing offices  \n<strong>3.</strong> Clean and accessible facilities  \n\n<strong>SAFETY AND SECURITY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Security guards on duty  \n<strong>2.</strong> CCTV monitoring  \n<strong>3.</strong> Emergency protocols in place  \n\n<strong>WANT TO SEE FOR YOURSELF?</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Visit during office hours (Monday to Saturday, 8:00 AM to 5:00 PM)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Contact the Admission Office to schedule a campus tour  \n\nWhich facilities are you most interested in learning about?	campus_facilities	68.43229793680868	2026-03-30 17:59:05.482245+08	\N
810	Phone number?	I'm glad you want to get in touch! Here's how you can contact Lipa City Colleges!\n\n<strong>OFFICIAL CONTACT INFORMATION:</strong>  \n<strong>PHONE NUMBERS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Main Line - Contact the Admission Office for the current number  \n<strong>2.</strong> Registrar - Contact for the specific number  \n<strong>3.</strong> Admission Office - Contact for the specific number  \n\n<strong>EMAIL:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Official Email - Check the website for the current email  \n<strong>2.</strong> Admission inquiries - Contact the Marketing or Admission Office  \n\n<strong>WEBSITE:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> https://www.lipacitycolleges.edu.ph/  \n<strong>2.</strong> Contains official information and updates  \n\n<strong>SOCIAL MEDIA:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Facebook - https://www.facebook.com/LeadershipCompetenceCommitment  \n<strong>2.</strong> Follow for announcements and news  \n\n<strong>PHYSICAL ADDRESS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Lipa City Colleges  \n<strong>2.</strong> G.A. Solis Street Lipa City, Batangas  \n\n<strong>OFFICE HOURS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Monday to Saturday: 8:00 AM to 5:00 PM  \n<strong>2.</strong> Closed on Sundays and holidays  \n\n<strong>SPECIFIC CONCERNS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Admission or Enrollment - Guidance and Admission Office  \n<strong>2.</strong> Tuition or Payments - Cashier's Office  \n<strong>3.</strong> Transcripts or Records - Registrar's Office  \n<strong>4.</strong> Scholarships - Marketing Office or Student Affairs  \n<strong>5.</strong> Academic Programs - Respective College or Department Offices  \n\n<strong>BEST WAY TO REACH US:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Visit in person (Monday to Saturday, 8:00 AM to 5:00 PM)  \nBest for detailed discussions  \n<strong>2.</strong> Call during office hours  \nBest for quick questions  \n<strong>3.</strong> Check the website  \nFor updated information  \n<strong>4.</strong> Send a Facebook message  \nFor social media inquiries  \n\n<strong>PRO TIP:</strong> If you are planning to visit, mornings (8:00 AM to 10:00 AM) are usually less crowded.\n\nWhat specific office would you like to contact? I can guide you!	contact_information	68.43229793680868	2026-03-30 17:59:26.85395+08	\N
