COPY public.chatbot_trainingdata (id, answer, is_active, created_at, updated_at, intent_id, is_reviewed, notes, office_id, questions_data, reviewed_at, reviewed_by_id, submitted_at, submitted_by_id) FROM stdin;
11	Good news! I can help you with that!\n<strong>Enrollment for the 2nd Semester starts on January 6, 2026!</strong>\n\nMark your calendar! It's best to enroll early to get your preferred schedule and avoid the rush.\n\nHere's a quick tip: Try to complete your requirements ahead of time so you can enroll on the first day. That way, you'll have more slots to choose from.\n\nWould you like to know what documents you need to prepare? Or maybe you're curious about the admission procedure? I'm happy to help you get ready! Just ask!	t	2026-02-17 20:16:29.341+08	2026-03-28 18:23:20.906025+08	45	t		\N	["When is enrollment?", "When does enrollment start?", "What is the enrollment schedule?", "Is enrollment open now?", "Until when is enrollment?", "Enrollment date", "When can I enroll?", "Enrollment period", "When to enroll?", "Enrollment start date", "Kailan ang enrollment?", "Kailan magsisimula ang enrollment?", "Ano ang schedule ng enrollment?", "Bukas na ba ang enrollment?", "Hanggang kailan ang enrollment?", "Petsa ng enrollment", "Kailan ako pwede mag-enroll?", "Panahon ng enrollment", "Kelan mag-enroll?", "Simula ng enrollment"]	\N	\N	2026-02-20 23:38:29.56+08	\N
2	Sure! Here's when you can visit our library!\n\n<strong>Library Hours:</strong>\n<strong>1.</strong> Monday to Saturday: <strong>8:00 AM to 5:00 PM</strong>  \n<strong>2.</strong> Closed on Sundays and holidays  \n\nThat's 9 hours a day to study, research, or borrow books! The library staff are very helpful too - they can assist you in finding references for your projects.\n\nDo you have any other questions? Maybe about our programs, admission requirements, or enrollment? I'm here to help!	t	2026-02-03 16:57:26.28+08	2026-03-28 18:27:36.520575+08	36	t		\N	["What are the library hours?", "What time does the library open?", "What time does the library close?", "Is the library open today?", "When is the library available?", "Library schedule", "Library opening hours", "When does library open?", "Library operating hours", "What time is library open?", "Ano ang oras ng library?", "Anong oras bubukas ang library?", "Anong oras magsasara ang library?", "Bukas ba ang library ngayon?", "Kailan available ang library?", "Schedule ng library", "Oras ng pagbubukas ng library", "Kelan bubuksan ang library?", "Operating hours ng library", "Anong oras bukas ang library?"]	\N	\N	2026-02-20 23:38:29.56+08	\N
62	Absolutely! We welcome transfer students! Here's everything you need to know about transferring to LCC!\n\n<strong>TRANSFEREE REQUIREMENTS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> <strong>Transcript of Records (TOR)</strong> from your previous college  \n<strong>2.</strong> <strong>Certificate of Eligibility to Transfer</strong> (if still enrolled)  \n<strong>3.</strong> <strong>Certificate of Good Moral Character</strong> from previous school  \n<strong>4.</strong> <strong>PSA Birth Certificate</strong> (original)  \n<strong>5.</strong> <strong>2-3 pieces of 2x2 ID photos</strong>  \n\n<strong>THE PROCESS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> <strong>Submit your TOR to the Registrar</strong>  \nThey will evaluate which subjects are creditable  \n\n<strong>2.</strong> <strong>Meet with your program's Dean</strong>  \nDiscuss your curriculum and required subjects  \n\n<strong>3.</strong> <strong>Submit admission requirements</strong>  \nFollow the same process as new students  \n\n<strong>4.</strong> <strong>Complete enrollment</strong>  \nPay fees and finalize your schedule  \n\n<strong>IMPORTANT THINGS TO KNOW:</strong>  \n\n<strong>SUBJECT CREDITING:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Not all subjects automatically transfer  \n<strong>2.</strong> The Registrar evaluates based on course content  \n<strong>3.</strong> Similar subjects may be credited  \n<strong>4.</strong> Some subjects may need to be retaken  \n\n<strong>PROCESSING TIME:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Getting TOR from previous school: 1 to 2 weeks  \n<strong>2.</strong> LCC evaluation: A few days to 1 week  \n\n<strong>BEST TIME TO TRANSFER:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Start of the semester (1st or 2nd semester)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Allows smoother transition  \n\n<strong>NEED MORE INFORMATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Contact the <strong>Registrar's Office</strong>  \n<strong>2.</strong> Contact the <strong>Dean</strong> of your chosen program  \n<strong>3.</strong> Visit: https://www.lipacitycol