75	Great question! Let me tell you about the Dr. Ricardo Bonilla Scholarship Program!\n\n<strong>WHAT IS IT:</strong>  \nThe Dr. Ricardo Bonilla Scholarship is named in honor of <strong>LCC's founder, Dr. Ricardo Bonilla</strong>. It is open to incoming college students who pass the scholarship examination based on standard or above average criteria.\n\n<strong>WHO CAN QUALIFY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Incoming college students  \n<strong>2.</strong> Must pass the LCC Scholarship Examination  \n<strong>3.</strong> Must meet the required performance criteria  \n\n<strong>SCHOLARSHIP BENEFITS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> 25% to 100% discount on tuition and miscellaneous fees  \n<strong>2.</strong> The percentage depends on examination performance  \n\n<strong>DURATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Renewable until program completion, provided requirements are maintained  \n\n<strong>HOW TO MAINTAIN THE SCHOLARSHIP:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> No grades lower than 2.25 in any subject  \n<strong>2.</strong> Maintain a GPA of 1.75 or higher  \n<strong>3.</strong> Remain in good standing with no disciplinary actions  \n<strong>4.</strong> Submit a certified true copy of your latest grades  \n\n<strong>RENEWAL BENEFITS (BASED ON GPA):</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> GPA 1.00 to 1.25 - 100% discount on tuition and miscellaneous fees  \n<strong>2.</strong> GPA 1.26 to 1.50 - 75% discount on tuition and miscellaneous fees  \n<strong>3.</strong> GPA 1.51 to 1.75 - 50% discount on tuition and miscellaneous fees  \n\n<strong>REQUIREMENTS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Pass the scholarship examination  \n<strong>2.</strong> Submit certified true copy of latest grades (for renewal)  \n\n<strong>WHERE TO APPLY OR TAKE THE EXAM:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Scholarships Office  \n<strong>2.</strong> Marketing Office  \n<strong>3.</strong> Admissions Office  \n\n<strong>PRO TIP:</strong>  \nThis scholarship covers both tuition and miscellaneous fees. Preparing w