61	No problem! Let me explain these documents for you!\n\n<strong>FORM 138 - Report Card:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Your grades from senior high school  \n<strong>2.</strong> Shows subjects you took and your performance  \n<strong>3.</strong> Get it from your previous school's registrar  \n\n<strong>FORM 137 - Permanent Record:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Your complete academic history (elementary to senior high)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Includes awards, attendance, and conduct records  \n<strong>3.</strong> More detailed than Form 138  \n\n<strong>PSA BIRTH CERTIFICATE:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Official birth certificate from the Philippine Statistics Authority  \n<strong>2.</strong> Has security features (not just a local copy)  \n<strong>3.</strong> Get it from PSA outlets or online: https://www.psahelpline.ph/  \n<strong>4.</strong> Costs around ₱155 per copy  \n\n<strong>CERTIFICATE OF GOOD MORAL CHARACTER:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Certifies you had good behavior in your previous school  \n<strong>2.</strong> Get it from your school principal or guidance office  \n<strong>3.</strong> Usually free or with minimal fee  \n\n<strong>TRANSCRIPT OF RECORDS (TOR):</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Required for transferees - contains your grades from previous college  \n<strong>2.</strong> Get it from your previous college's registrar  \n<strong>3.</strong> May take 1 to 2 weeks to process  \n\n<strong>GOOD MORAL CHARACTER (FOR TRANSFEREES):</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Certifies you have no disciplinary issues  \n<strong>2.</strong> Required for transferees  \n\n<strong>WHERE TO GET THESE DOCUMENTS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Forms 137 and 138 - Your senior high school registrar  \n<strong>2.</strong> PSA Birth Certificate - PSA outlets or online  \n<strong>3.</strong> Good Moral Certificate - School principal or guidance office  \n<strong>4.</strong> TOR - Previous college registrar (for transferees)  \n\nNeed help with anything else about