71	Wonderful choice! Let me tell you about our Education programs!\n\n<strong>YES, WE OFFER THREE EDUCATION PROGRAMS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> <strong>Bachelor of Elementary Education (BEED)</strong>  \n<strong>2.</strong> <strong>Bachelor of Secondary Education (BSED)</strong>  \n<strong>3.</strong> <strong>Bachelor of Arts in Psychology (AB-PSY)</strong>  \n\n<strong>BEED - ELEMENTARY EDUCATION:</strong>  \n<strong>FOCUS:</strong> Teach learners in Grades 1 to 6  \n\n<strong>DURATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> 4 years  \n\n<strong>WHAT YOU WILL STUDY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Child and Adolescent Development  \n<strong>2.</strong> Teaching methods for all subjects  \n<strong>3.</strong> Classroom Management  \n<strong>4.</strong> Educational Psychology  \n<strong>5.</strong> Teaching methods in Mathematics, Science, English, and Filipino  \n<strong>6.</strong> Practicum and Student Teaching  \n\n<strong>CAREER OPPORTUNITIES:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Elementary School Teacher (public or private)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Tutorial Center Teacher  \n<strong>3.</strong> School Administrator (with experience)  \n<strong>4.</strong> Educational Consultant  \n<strong>5.</strong> Curriculum Developer  \n\n<strong>AFTER GRADUATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Take the Licensure Examination for Teachers (LET)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Become a Licensed Teacher  \n\n<strong>BSED - SECONDARY EDUCATION:</strong>  \n<strong>FOCUS:</strong> Teach learners in Grades 7 to 12  \n\n<strong>DURATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> 4 years  \n\n<strong>CHOOSE YOUR MAJOR:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> English  \n<strong>2.</strong> Mathematics  \n<strong>3.</strong> Filipino  \n<strong>4.</strong> Science  \n\n<strong>WHAT YOU WILL STUDY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Major subject specialization  \n<strong>2.</strong> Teaching methodologies  \n<strong>3.</strong> Adolescent Psychology  \n<strong>4.</strong> Curriculum Development  \n<strong>5.</strong> Assessment and Evaluation  \n<strong>6.</strong> Student Teaching or Practicum  \n\n<strong>CAREER OPPORTUNITIES:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> High School Teacher (public or private)  \n<strong>2.</strong> College Professor (with Master's degree)  \n<strong>3.</strong> Review Center Teacher  \n<strong>4.</strong> School Administrator  \n<strong>5.</strong> Educational Materials Writer  \n\n<strong>AFTER GRADUATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Take the Licensure Examination for Teachers (LET)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Become a Licensed Teacher  \n\n<strong>AB-PSY - PSYCHOLOGY:</strong>  \n<strong>FOCUS:</strong> Understanding human behavior  \n\n<strong>DURATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> 4 years  \n\n<strong>WHAT YOU WILL STUDY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> General Psychology  \n<strong>2.</strong> Developmental Psychology  \n<strong>3.</strong> Abnormal Psychology  \n<strong>4.</strong> Social Psychology  \n<strong>5.</strong> Industrial and Organizational Psychology  \n<strong>6.</strong> Psychological Testing  \n<strong>7.</strong> Counseling Techniques  \n<strong>8.</strong> Research Methods  \n\n<strong>CAREER OPPORTUNITIES:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Human Resource Specialist or Recruiter  \n<strong>2.</strong> Organizational Development Specialist  \n<strong>3.</strong> Market Research Analyst  \n<strong>4.</strong> Guidance Counselor (with Master's degree)  \n<strong>5.</strong> Psychology Professor  \n<strong>6.</strong> Research Assistant  \n<strong>7.</strong> Training and Development Officer  \n\n<strong>NOTE:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> To become a licensed Psychologist or Guidance Counselor, a Master's degree is required  \n\n<strong>WHY CHOOSE EDUCATION AT LCC:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Experienced faculty members  \n<strong>2.</strong> Practice teaching opportunities  \n<strong>3.</strong> Strong LET board exam performance  \n<strong>4.</strong> Partner schools for practicum  \n<strong>5.</strong> Affordable and quality education  \n\n<strong>SALARY POTENTIAL:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Public School Teacher: ₱25,000 to ₱50,000+ per month  \n<strong>2.</strong> Private School Teacher: ₱15,000 to ₱40,000 per month  \n<strong>3.</strong> Psychology Graduate: ₱18,000 to ₱45,000+ per month  \n<strong>4.</strong> Teaching abroad: $2,000 to $5,000+ per month  \n\n<strong>WHICH PROGRAM TO CHOOSE:</strong>  \n\n<strong>CHOOSE BEED IF:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> You enjoy working with young children  \n<strong>2.</strong> You want to teach all subjects  \n<strong>3.</strong> You enjoy creative and interactive teaching  \n\n<strong>CHOOSE BSED IF:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> You have a favorite subject to specialize in  \n<strong>2.</strong> You enjoy working with teenagers  \n<strong>3.</strong> You want deeper subject expertise  \n\n<strong>CHOOSE AB-PSY IF:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> You are interested in human behavior  \n<strong>2.</strong> You want a career in human resources or counseling  \n<strong>3.</strong> You prefer flexible career paths  \n\n<strong>NEXT STEPS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Ask about admission requirements  \n<strong>2.</strong> Ask about tuition fees for Education programs  \n<strong>3.</strong> Ask about enrollment schedule  \n\nTeaching is a meaningful profession that allows you to make a lasting impact on others.	t	2026-03-29 13:46:35.268441+08	2026-03-29 14:17:57.316944+08	86	f		\N	["What is Education?", "What is BEED?", "Tell me about Education programs", "What is Education program like?", "Ano ang Education program?", "What is BSED?", "How long is Education?", "Ano ang BEED?", "What is Elementary Education?", "Ano ang Secondary Education program?", "What is teaching course like?", "What will I study in Education?", "Jobs after Education?", "Ano ang teaching course?", "Tell me about BSED", "BEED or BSED?", "What majors in BSED?", "Career in Education?", "Why study Education at LCC?", "What is Psychology course?"]	\N	\N	2026-03-29 13:46:35