72	Fantastic choice! Let me tell you about our Hospitality and Tourism programs!\n\n<strong>YES, WE OFFER TWO PROGRAMS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> <strong>Bachelor of Science in Hospitality Management (BSHM)</strong>  \n<strong>2.</strong> <strong>Bachelor of Science in Tourism Management (BSTM)</strong>  \n\n<strong>BSHM - HOSPITALITY MANAGEMENT:</strong>  \n<strong>FOCUS:</strong> Hotels, restaurants, and events  \n\n<strong>DURATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> 4 years (8 semesters)  \n\n<strong>WHAT YOU WILL STUDY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Hotel and Restaurant Management  \n<strong>2.</strong> Food and Beverage Service  \n<strong>3.</strong> Front Office Operations  \n<strong>4.</strong> Housekeeping Management  \n<strong>5.</strong> Culinary Arts fundamentals  \n<strong>6.</strong> Event Management  \n<strong>7.</strong> Customer Service Excellence  \n<strong>8.</strong> Food Safety and Sanitation  \n<strong>9.</strong> Bar and Beverage Management  \n\n<strong>HANDS-ON TRAINING:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Kitchen and culinary laboratories  \n<strong>2.</strong> Restaurant simulation  \n<strong>3.</strong> Hotel operations practice  \n<strong>4.</strong> On-the-job training in hotels and restaurants  \n<strong>5.</strong> Event planning and execution  \n\n<strong>CAREER OPPORTUNITIES:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Hotel Manager or Supervisor  \n<strong>2.</strong> Restaurant Manager  \n<strong>3.</strong> Event Coordinator or Planner  \n<strong>4.</strong> Food Service Manager  \n<strong>5.</strong> Bar Manager  \n<strong>6.</strong> Cruise ship staff  \n<strong>7.</strong> Catering Manager  \n<strong>8.</strong> Opportunities in international hotels and resorts  \n\n<strong>BSTM - TOURISM MANAGEMENT:</strong>  \n<strong>FOCUS:</strong> Travel, tours, and tourism industry  \n\n<strong>DURATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> 4 years (8 semesters)  \n\n<strong>WHAT YOU WILL STUDY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Tourism Planning and Development  \n<strong>2.</strong> Tour Operations Management  \n<strong>3.</strong> Travel Agency Management  \n<strong>4.</strong> Tourist Destination Management  \n<strong>5.</strong> Transportation Management  \n<strong>6.</strong> Tourism Marketing  \n<strong>7.</strong> Event Management  \n<strong>8.</strong> Heritage and Cultural Tourism  \n<strong>9.</strong> Ecotourism and Sustainable Tourism  \n\n<strong>TRAINING:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Tour guiding practice  \n<strong>2.</strong> Travel agency operations  \n<strong>3.</strong> Familiarization tours  \n<strong>4.</strong> Event planning  \n<strong>5.</strong> On-the-job training in tourism offices and travel agencies  \n\n<strong>CAREER OPPORTUNITIES:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Travel Agent or Consultant  \n<strong>2.</strong> Tour Guide or Tour Manager  \n<strong>3.</strong> Resort Manager  \n<strong>4.</strong> Tourism Officer  \n<strong>5.</strong> Travel Content Creator  \n<strong>6.</strong> Destination Marketing Manager  \n<strong>7.</strong> Cruise line management  \n<strong>8.</strong> International tourism operations  \n\n<strong>WHAT IS THE DIFFERENCE:</strong>  \n\n<strong>BSHM - FOCUS:</strong> Hotels, restaurants, and food services  \n<strong>1.</strong> Suitable for those interested in hospitality and service  \n<strong>2.</strong> Work in hotels, restaurants, resorts, and events  \n<strong>3.</strong> More hands-on in food and service operations  \n\n<strong>BSTM - FOCUS:</strong> Travel and tourism management  \n<strong>1.</strong> Suitable for those interested in travel and culture  \n<strong>2.</strong> Work in travel agencies, airlines, and tourism offices  \n<strong>3.</strong> Focus on planning trips and promoting destinations  \n\n<strong>WHY CHOOSE HOSPITALITY OR TOURISM AT LCC:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Modern hospitality laboratories  \n<strong>2.</strong> Industry-experienced faculty  \n<strong>3.</strong> On-the-job training placements  \n<strong>4.</strong> Event management opportunities  \n<strong>5.</strong> Strong industry connections  \n<strong>6.</strong> Hands-on learning experience  \n\n<strong>SALARY POTENTIAL:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Entry Level: ₱15,000 to ₱25,000 per month  \n<strong>2.</strong> Experienced: ₱30,000 to ₱70,000+ per month  \n<strong>3.</strong> Abroad: $1,500 to $5,000+ per month  \n<strong>4.</strong> Cruise ship work may include accommodation and travel benefits  \n\n<strong>PERFECT FOR:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> People-oriented individuals  \n<strong>2.</strong> Those who enjoy service and hospitality  \n<strong>3.</strong> Individuals who enjoy travel and adventure  \n<strong>4.</strong> Cultural enthusiasts  \n<strong>5.</strong> Creative and organized individuals  \n\n<strong>NEXT STEPS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Ask about admission requirements  \n<strong>2.</strong> Ask about tuition fees for Hospitality or Tourism  \n<strong>3.</strong> Ask about the difference between BSHM and BSTM  \n\nHospitality and Tourism offer exciting opportunities both locally and internationally.	t	2026-03-29 13:46:35.271555+08	2026-03-29 14:19:17.130367+08	87	f		\N	["What is Hospitality Management?", "What is BSHM?", "Tell me about Hospitality programs", "What is Hospitality program like?", "Ano ang HRM program?", "What is Tourism Management?", "How long is Hospitality?", "Ano ang BSHM?", "What is BSTM?", "Ano ang Tourism program?", "Hotel Management program details", "What will I study in Hospitality?", "Jobs after Hospitality?", "Ano ang Tourism course?", "Tell me about BSTM", "BSHM or BSTM?", "What is Tourism?", "Career in Hospitality?", "Why study Hospitality at LCC?", "Hotel and Restaurant Management?"]	\N	\N	2026-03-29 13:46:35.271555+08	\N
84	Yes! Let me tell you about the Pag-Ibig Fund Loyalty Card Discount!\n\n<strong>WHAT IS IT:</strong>  \nLCC offers a tuition discount to students whose parent or guardian is a Pag-Ibig Fund (HDMF) Loyalty Card holder.\n\n<strong>WHO CAN QUALIFY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Students whose parent or guardian has a Pag-Ibig Loyalty Card  \n<strong>2.</strong> Students who personally have a Pag-Ibig Loyalty Card  \n\n<strong>BENEFITS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> 15% discount on tuition fee for new students  \n<strong>2.</strong> 10% discount on tuition fee for continuing students  \n\n<strong>WHAT IT COVERS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Tuition fee only  \n<strong>2.</strong> Does not include miscellaneous fees  \n\n<strong>DURATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Renewable until program completion  \n\n<strong>HOW TO MAINTAIN THE DISCOUNT:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> No failing grades  \n<strong>2.</strong> Maintain good standing with no disciplinary records  \n<strong>3.</strong> Submit certified true copy of latest grades  \n\n<strong>RENEWAL BENEFITS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> 10% to 15% discount on tuition fee depending on student status  \n\n<strong>REQUIREMENTS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Pag-Ibig Fund Loyalty Card (original and photocopy)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Latest grades (Form 138)  \n<strong>3.</strong> Scholarship or discount application form  \n\n<strong>WHERE TO APPLY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Marketing Office  \n<strong>2.</strong> Scholarships Office  \n\n<strong>IF YOU DO NOT HAVE A PAG-IBIG LOYALTY CARD:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Visit the nearest Pag-Ibig Fund (HDMF) branch  \n<strong>2.</strong> Check their requirements for Loyalty Card issuance  \n\n<strong>EXAMPLE SAVINGS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> If tuition is ₱20,000:  \n<strong>2.</strong> New student pays ₱17,000 with 15% discount  \n<strong>3.</strong> Continuing student pays ₱18,000 with 10% discount  \n\n<strong>NOTE:</strong>  \nEven a smal