68	Great choice! Let me tell you about our Criminology program!\n\n<strong>WHAT IS IT?</strong>  \nBachelor of Science in Criminology is a 4-year program that prepares you for careers in law enforcement, criminal investigation, crime prevention, and the justice system.\n\n<strong>PROGRAM HIGHLIGHTS:</strong>  \n\n<strong>DURATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> 4 years (8 semesters)  \n\n<strong>WHAT YOU WILL STUDY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Criminal Law and Jurisprudence  \n<strong>2.</strong> Criminalistics (Forensic Science)  \n<strong>3.</strong> Criminal Investigation and Detection  \n<strong>4.</strong> Law Enforcement Operations  \n<strong>5.</strong> Correctional Administration  \n<strong>6.</strong> Crime Prevention and Control  \n<strong>7.</strong> Criminology Theories  \n<strong>8.</strong> Physical Fitness and Self-Defense  \n\n<strong>TRAINING COMPONENTS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Physical fitness training  \n<strong>2.</strong> Firearms and tactics  \n<strong>3.</strong> Crime scene investigation  \n<strong>4.</strong> Interview and interrogation techniques  \n<strong>5.</strong> Law enforcement procedures  \n\n<strong>AFTER GRADUATION:</strong>  \n\n<strong>LICENSURE EXAM:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Take the Criminologist Licensure Examination conducted by PRC  \n<strong>2.</strong> Passing the exam allows you to become a Licensed Criminologist  \n\n<strong>CAREER OPPORTUNITIES:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Police Officer (Philippine National Police)  \n<strong>2.</strong> NBI Agent (National Bureau of Investigation)  \n<strong>3.</strong> PDEA Agent (Anti-Drug Operations)  \n<strong>4.</strong> BIR or BOC Agent  \n<strong>5.</strong> Security Management  \n<strong>6.</strong> Private Investigator  \n<strong>7.</strong> Court Personnel  \n<strong>8.</strong> Corporate Security Director  \n<strong>9.</strong> Criminology Professor  \n\n<strong>REQUIREMENTS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Must meet physical fitness standards  \n<strong>2.</strong> Good moral character (strictly evaluated)  \n<strong>3.</strong> No criminal record  \n<strong>4.</strong> May have height requirements (check with the department)  \n\n<strong>WHY CHOOSE CRIMINOLOGY AT LCC:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Experienced law enforcement faculty  \n<strong>2.</strong> Training facilities available  \n<strong>3.</strong> Strong alumni network in police and military  \n<strong>4.</strong> Excellent board exam passing rate  \n<strong>5.</strong> Career placement assistance  \n\n<strong>SALARY POTENTIAL:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Police Officer: ₱30,000 to ₱50,000+ per month  \n<strong>2.</strong> NBI or PDEA Agent: ₱40,000 to ₱70,000+ per month  \n<strong>3.</strong> Security Management: ₱25,000 to ₱100,000+ per month  \n\n<strong>NEXT STEPS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Ask about admission requirements for Criminology  \n<strong>2.</strong> Ask about tuition fees for Criminology  \n<strong>3.</strong> Contact the College of Criminal Justice for physical requirements  \n\nCriminology is a great choice if you are interested in serving and protecting the community.	t	2026-03-29 13:46:35.245633+08	2026-03-29 14:06:30.576991+08	83	f		\N	["What is Criminology?", "What is BSCRIM?", "Tell me about Criminology", "What is Criminology program like?", "Ano ang Criminology program?", "What is BS Criminology?", "How long is Criminology?", "Ano ang Criminology?", "Ano ang meron sa Criminology program?", "Criminology program details", "What will I study in Criminology?", "Jobs after Criminology?", "What is Criminology program?", "Tell me about BSCRIM", "What is BSCRIM program like?", "Criminology course info", "What is Bachelor of Science in Criminology?", "Career in Criminology?", "Subjects in Criminology?", "Why study Criminology at LCC?"]	\N	\N	2026-03-29 13:46:35.245633+08	\N
73	Excellent! Let me tell you about our Academic Scholarship Program!\n\n<strong>WHAT IS IT:</strong>  \nThe Academic Scholarship is awarded to students who are among the <strong>top five (5)</strong> of their graduating batch or class based on their general average.\n<strong>WHO CAN QUALIFY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Top 1 (Valedictorian)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Top 2 (Salutatorian)  \n<strong>3.</strong> Top 3  \n<strong>4.</strong> Top 4  \n<strong>5.</strong> Top 5  \n\n<strong>SCHOLARSHIP BENEFITS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Rank 1 - 100% discount on tuition and miscellaneous fees  \n<strong>2.</strong> Rank 2 - 75% discount on tuition and miscellaneous fees  \n<strong>3.</strong> Rank 3 - 50% discount on tuition and miscellaneous fees  \n<strong>4.</strong> Rank 4 - 30% discount on tuition and miscellaneous fees  \n<strong>5.</strong> Rank 5 - 20% discount on tuition and miscellaneous fees  \n\n<strong>DURATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Renewable until program completion, provided requirements are maintained  \n\n<strong>HOW TO MAINTAIN THE SCHOLARSHIP:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> No grades lower than 2.25 in any subject  \n<strong>2.</strong> Maintain a GPA of 1.75 or higher  \n<strong>3.</strong> Remain in good standing with no disciplinary actions  \n<strong>4.</strong> Submit a certified true copy of your latest grades  \n\n<strong>RENEWAL BENEFITS (BASED ON GPA):</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> GPA 1.00 to 1.25 - 100% discount  \n<strong>2.</strong> GPA 1.26 to 1.50 - 75% discount  \n<strong>3.</strong> GPA 1.51 to 1.75 - 50% discount  \n\n<strong>REQUIREMENTS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Certified true copy of latest grades (Form 138)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Proof of ranking (Top 1 to 5)  \n\n<strong>WHERE TO APPLY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Scholarships Office or Marketing Office  \n\n<strong>PRO TIP:</strong>  \nThis scholarship covers both tuition and miscellaneous fees, making it more comprehensive than many other schola