plinary records  \n<strong>3.</strong> Submit certified true copy of latest grades during renewal  \n\n<strong>REQUIREMENTS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Barangay Certificate as proof of residence  \n<strong>2.</strong> Latest grades (Form 138)  \n<strong>3.</strong> Scholarship application form  \n\n<strong>WHERE TO APPLY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Marketing Office  \n<strong>2.</strong> Scholarships Office  \n\n<strong>CAN YOU APPLY FOR BOTH:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Only one institutional scholarship can be availed at a time  \n<strong>2.</strong> External or government scholarships may still be combined  \n\n<strong>WHICH ONE SHOULD YOU APPLY FOR:</strong>  \n\n<strong>CHOOSE AYOUDA IF:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> You are from a distant area  \n<strong>2.</strong> You travel far to attend school  \n\n<strong>CHOOSE BEAP IF:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> You are from an area affected by the Taal Volcano eruption  \n<strong>2.</strong> Your family was impacted by the event  \n\n<strong>GOOD NEWS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> A 50% discount means you only pay half of the tuition fee  \n<strong>2.</strong> Combined with payment plans, education becomes more affordable  \n\nWould you like to know about other scholarships you might qualify for? Just ask!	t	2026-03-29 20:22:17.846235+08	2026-03-29 20:33:39.563509+08	92	f		\N	["What is AYOUDA?", "What is BEAP?", "Tell me about AYOUDA", "Tell me about BEAP", "Ano ang AYOUDA?", "Ano ang BEAP?", "AYOUDA scholarship", "BEAP scholarship", "Scholarship for distant areas", "Taal eruption scholarship", "Scholarship for affected areas", "AYOUDA requirements", "BEAP requirements", "How to get AYOUDA?", "How to get BEAP?", "What is 50% scholarship like?", "Distance-based scholarship", "Batangan Educational Alalay Program", "Assistance to Youth Defying Adversities", "Tulong sa estudyante sa malayo"]	\N	\N	2026-03-29 20:22:17.846235+08	\N
79	Great questions! Let me explain both the Alumni Discount and Family Privilege!\n\n<strong>ALUMNI DISCOUNT:</strong>  \n\n<strong>WHAT IS IT:</strong>  \nA discount for students whose parent graduated from LCC or LCC Silvercrest.\n\n<strong>WHO CAN QUALIFY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Parent is a graduate of LCC or LCC Silvercrest  \n<strong>2.</strong> Applies to any program or level  \n\n<strong>BENEFITS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> 20% discount on tuition fee  \n\n<strong>HOW TO MAINTAIN:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> No failing grades  \n<strong>2.</strong> Maintain good standing with no disciplinary issues  \n<strong>3.</strong> Submit latest grades for renewal  \n\n<strong>REQUIREMENTS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Parent's Alumni Certificate or diploma  \n<strong>2.</strong> Latest grades (Form 138)  \n<strong>3.</strong> Scholarship application form  \n\n<strong>FAMILY PRIVILEGE:</strong>  \n\n<strong>WHAT IS IT:</strong>  \nA special discount for families with three or more siblings enrolled at the same time.\n\n<strong>WHO CAN QUALIFY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Three or more siblings enrolled simultaneously  \n<strong>2.</strong> Can be in LCC or Silvercrest  \n<strong>3.</strong> Must be enrolled in the same school year  \n\n<strong>BENEFITS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Third sibling receives 50% discount on tuition  \n<strong>2.</strong> Fourth sibling receives 75% discount on tuition  \n\n<strong>IMPORTANT RULES:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> The first two siblings must pay full tuition  \n<strong>2.</strong> Only the third and fourth siblings receive discounts  \n\n<strong>EXAMPLE:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> First sibling pays full tuition  \n<strong>2.</strong> Second sibling pays full tuition  \n<strong>3.</strong> Third sibling receives 50% discount  \n<strong>4.</strong> Fourth sibling receives 75% discount  \n\n<strong>DURATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Renewable as long as all siblings remain enrolled simultaneously  \n\n<strong>WHAT HAPPENS IF CONDITIONS CHANGE:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> If one sibling graduates, the discount adjusts  \n<strong>2.</strong> If only two remain, the discount is no longer applicable  \n\n<strong>CAN YOU AVAIL BOTH:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Only one institutional scholarship or discount is allowed at a time  \n<strong>2.</strong> Choose the option that provides greater savings  \n\n<strong>WHICH SHOULD YOU CHOOSE:</strong>  \n\n<strong>CHOOSE ALUMNI DISCOUNT IF:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Your parent graduated from LCC  \n<strong>2.</strong> You do not have three or more siblings enrolled  \n<strong>3.</strong> You prefer a consistent 20% discount  \n\n<strong>CHOOSE FAMILY PRIVILEGE IF:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> You have three or more siblings enrolled together  \n<strong>2.</strong> You are the third or fourth sibling  \n<strong>3.</strong> You want a higher discount (50% to 75%)  \n\n<strong>SAMPLE SAVINGS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Without discount: ₱80,000 total for four siblings  \n<strong>2.</strong> With Family Privilege: ₱55,000 total  \n<strong>3.</strong> Total savings: ₱25,000 per semester  \n\n<strong>WHERE TO APPLY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Marketing Office  \n<strong>2.</strong> Scholarships Office  \n\n<strong>REQUIREMENTS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Proof of relationship (birth certificates)  \n<strong>2.</strong> Assessment forms showing all siblings enrolled  \n<strong>3.</strong> Latest grades  \n\n<strong>NOTE:</strong>  \nThese programs are designed to support families and reduce the cost of education.\n\nNeed help choosing which discount is best for you? Just ask!	t	2026-03-29 20:22:17.863842+08	2026-03-29 20:35:44.315609+08	94	f		\N	["What is Alumni Discount?", "What is Family Privilege?", "Alumni scholarship", "Family Privilege scholarship", "Sibling discount", "Discount for LCC alumni children", "Alumni Discount requirements", "Family Privilege requirements", "How many siblings for discount?", "Discount kung graduate ng LCC ang magulang", "Discount para sa magkakapatid", "Alumni benefits for children", "Family Privilege details", "Sibling scholarship", "Discount for multiple enrollees", "Kapatid discount", "Graduate parent discount", "3 siblings discount", "Multiple family members discount", "Ano ang Family Privilege?"]	\N	\N	2026-03-29 20:22:17.863842+08	\N
81	Absolutely! Let me tell you about the PWD Discount!\n\n<strong>WHAT IS IT:</strong>  \nThis is a special discount for students with disabilities. LCC supports inclusive education and aims to make learning accessible to everyone.\n\n<strong>WHO CAN QUALIFY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Students with any form of disability  \n<strong>2.</strong> Must have a valid PWD ID or proof of disability  \n\n<strong>BENEFITS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> 20% discount on tuition fee  \n\n<strong>WHAT IT COVERS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Tuition fee only  \n<strong>2.</strong> Does not include miscellaneous fees  \n\n<strong>DURATION:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Renewable until program completion  \n\n<strong>HOW TO MAINTAIN THE DISCOUNT:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> No failing grades  \n<strong>2.</strong> Maintain good standing with no disciplinary records  \n<strong>3.</strong> Submit certified true copy of latest grades  \n\n<strong>REQUIREMENTS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> PWD ID issued by the local government  \n<strong>2.</strong> Latest grades (Form 138)  \n<strong>3.</strong> Scholarship application form  \n\n<strong>HOW TO GET A PWD ID:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Visit the City or Municipal Social Welfare and Development Office  \n<strong>2.</strong> Provide a medical certificate or proof of disability  \n<strong>3.</strong> Processing time may vary depending on the local government unit  \n\n<strong>WHERE TO APPLY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Marketing Office  \n<strong>2.</strong> Scholarships Office  \n\n<strong>CAN YOU COMBINE WITH OTHER SCHOLARSHIPS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Only one institutional discount is allowed at a time  \n<strong>2.</strong> Can be combined with government or external scholarships  \n\n<strong>EXAMPLE SAVINGS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> If tuition is ₱20,000, a 20% discount reduces it to ₱16,000  \n<strong>2.</strong> Savings of ₱4,000 per semester  \n\n<strong>NOTE:</strong>  \nThis program supports inclusive education and ensures that students with disabilities have access to quality learning opportunities.\n\nWould you like to know about other scholarships or support services available? Just ask!	t	2026-03-29 20:22:17.876783+08	2026-03-29 20:37:24.754989+08	96	f		\N	["What is PWD Discount?", "Person with Disability discount", "Disability discount LCC", "PWD scholarship", "Ano ang PWD Discount?", "Discount for PWD students", "PWD Discount requirements", "How to get PWD Discount?", "Discount kung may kapansanan", "Scholarship for students with disability", "PWD student benefit", "What is 20% discount PWD?", "Paano makakuha ng PWD discount?", "PWD Discount details", "What is discount for disabled students?", "May scholarship ba para sa PWD?", "PWD Discount benefits", "Disability scholarship LCC", "PWD Discount application", "Special needs student discount"]	\N	\N	2026-03-29 20:22:17.876783+08	\N
