85	Great news for athletes! Let me tell you about the Athletics Scholarship!\n\n<strong>WHAT IS IT:</strong>  \nThe Athletics Scholarship is awarded to student-athletes who demonstrate strong athletic performance and represent LCC in sports competitions.\n\n<strong>WHO CAN QUALIFY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Talented student-athletes with strong sports performance  \n<strong>2.</strong> Students who represent or qualify to represent LCC in competitions  \n<strong>3.</strong> Must maintain both academic and athletic requirements  \n\n<strong>BENEFITS:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Tuition fee discount based on athletic performance and evaluation  \n\n<strong>HOW TO APPLY OR BE CONSIDERED:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Contact the Sports Office or Student Affairs Office  \n<strong>2.</strong> Participate in athletic evaluation or tryouts  \n<strong>3.</strong> Submit required documents  \n\n<strong>WHERE TO APPLY:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Sports Organizations Section or Student Affairs Office  \n<strong>2.</strong> Scholarships Office for processing  \n\n<strong>IMPORTANT NOTES:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Details on sports, tryout schedules, and discount rates may vary  \n<strong>2.</strong> Refer to the Student Handbook or contact the office directly for updated information  \n\n<strong>SPORTS OFFERED MAY INCLUDE:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Basketball  \n<strong>2.</strong> Volleyball  \n<strong>3.</strong> Football or Soccer  \n<strong>4.</strong> Swimming  \n<strong>5.</strong> Tennis  \n<strong>6.</strong> Martial arts  \n<strong>7.</strong> Other available sports  \n\n<strong>HOW TO MAINTAIN THE SCHOLARSHIP:</strong>  \n<strong>1.</strong> Maintain required academic performance  \n<strong>2.</strong> Actively participate in the team or sport  \n<strong>3.</strong> Maintain good standing with no disciplinary records  \n<strong>4.</strong> Represent LCC in competitions when required  \n\n<strong>NOTE:</strong>  \nThis scholarship allows st